[ Both Speaking Italian ]

22:44.324 --> 22:47.293
- This is so good of you.
- Don't say it again.

22:51.164 --> 22:54.327
Now that you're a double agent
and we're going to string my dad along,

22:54.401 --> 22:57.165
what if we were to buy
a car with your expense money ?

22:57.237 --> 22:59.501
- Okay.
- Great.

22:59.573 --> 23:01.700
- Hello, Tom.
- Hello.

23:01.775 --> 23:04.073
Marge, Marge,
what do you think ?

23:04.144 --> 23:06.305
Little Ciquencento
with my dad's money ?

23:06.379 --> 23:09.246
Oh, please, Dickie.
You can't even drive a car.

23:09.316 --> 23:12.649
- [ Tom ] You can't even drive.
- What we need urgently is an icebox.

23:12.719 --> 23:15.449
What do you think ? Agree with me,
and I'll be your friend for life.

23:16.556 --> 23:20.151
- I absolutely agree with Marge.
- Hmm.

23:20.227 --> 23:22.661
Icebox. Icebox.

23:26.499 --> 23:28.729
[ Bell Tolling ]

23:34.941 --> 23:37.068
[ Marge ]
So, what, is he gonna move in with you ?

23:37.143 --> 23:41.807
It'll just be for a little while.
He can be-- He makes me laugh.

23:41.882 --> 23:45.409
- Okay, darling.
- Promise you'd say ?

23:45.485 --> 23:49.319
- No, I like him.
- Marge, you like everybody.

23:49.389 --> 23:52.119
Don't like you.
[ Chuckles ]

23:52.192 --> 23:54.683
Then I'll go to your place
and you can move in with Tom.

24:04.042 --> 24:05.976
[ Imitating Marge ]
I like him.

24:06.044 --> 24:09.707
[ Imitating Dickie ]
Marge, you like everybody.

24:13.985 --> 24:16.886
[ Imitating Marge ]
No, I like him.

24:16.955 --> 24:21.824
[ Imitating Dickie ]
Marge, you like everybody.

24:21.893 --> 24:25.420
[ Dickie ] Now you'll find out why Miss
Sherwood always shows up for breakfast.

24:25.497 --> 24:28.091
It's not love.
It's my coffee machine.

24:28.166 --> 24:30.896
[ Marge ] Ever since Ermalinda
showed him how to make his own espresso,

24:30.969 --> 24:33.233
he feels like quite
the grownup.

24:33.304 --> 24:36.068
-I bought the coffee machine.
-[ Marge ] Oh, darling, is that for me ?

24:36.141 --> 24:38.473
This is for Tom,
because he didn't complain.

24:38.543 --> 24:41.376
[ Tom ]
That ring is superb.

24:41.446 --> 24:43.914
Oh, Tom, I love you.
See ?

24:43.982 --> 24:49.010
Ooh ! I had to promise,
capital "P," never to take it off.

24:49.087 --> 24:52.420
-Otherwise, I'd give it to you.
-Isn't it great ? I found it in Naples.

24:52.490 --> 24:55.050
I had to bargain for it
for about two weeks.

24:55.126 --> 24:57.560
I hope it wasn't cheap,
Marge.

24:57.629 --> 25:00.564
- Oh, it was.
- [ Chuckles ]

25:00.632 --> 25:04.227
I have to get a birthday present for
Frances, so perhaps you could help me.

25:04.302 --> 25:07.135
- Who's Frances ?
- My fiancee.

25:07.205 --> 25:10.038
Engaged ?
You're a dark horse, Ripley.

25:10.108 --> 25:12.042
- Who is she ?
- Your parents met her.

25:12.110 --> 25:16.012
Oh, God.
Oh, I can just imagine.

25:16.080 --> 25:18.275
"If only Dickie
would settle down.

25:18.349 --> 25:20.408
Doesn't every parent
deserve a grandchild ?"

25:20.485 --> 25:23.318
Oh, God.
Never. Never.

25:23.388 --> 25:27.950
I swear on your ring, Marge,
I'm never going back.

25:28.026 --> 25:30.551
- [ Tom ] Say when to pull.
- [ Dickie ] Pull now. Pull.

25:30.628 --> 25:34.462
It's not pulling.
I'm doing it wrong.

25:36.301 --> 25:38.633
- Better now, huh ?
- Okay, okay, okay.

25:38.703 --> 25:40.637
We'll make a sailor
of you yet.

25:40.705 --> 25:43.071
You're doing really well.

25:43.141 --> 25:46.372
- All right. Bar's open.
- Yes, please.

25:46.444 --> 25:49.572
- Hey, can we sail to Venice ?
- Sure. I love Venice.

25:51.683 --> 25:54.345
"See Venice and die."
Isn't that right ? Or is it Rome ?

25:54.419 --> 25:57.513
- Is it Rome ?
- I have to see Venice.

25:57.589 --> 26:01.423
You do something and die, don't you ?
Okay. Venice is on the list.

26:01.493 --> 26:04.053
And Rome.

26:04.128 --> 26:06.153
Do you ski ?

26:08.433 --> 26:11.163
Ah, no, no.
Don't tell me.

26:11.236 --> 26:14.501
You're a lost cause.
That's the next thing to deal with.

26:14.572 --> 26:17.200
Christmas, we're planning
a skiing trip to Cortina.

26:17.275 --> 26:20.676
- Excellent skiing. Excellent. Marge.
- Yes ?

26:20.745 --> 26:23.441
Unbelievable.
Tom can't ski either.

26:23.515 --> 26:26.678
- We'll have to teach him that too.
- Thank you.

26:28.786 --> 26:31.983
Such low class, Marge.
Does this guy know anything ?

26:32.056 --> 26:34.320
Good thing we're not
getting married soon.

26:34.392 --> 26:37.122
We'd have to invite Tom
on our honeymoon.

26:40.398 --> 26:43.333
[ Marge ] Oh, I hated New York.
That whole Park Avenue crowd.

26:43.401 --> 26:45.392
So I fled to Paris
to work on my book.

26:45.470 --> 26:48.564
And I was always going
to this cafe in Monmartre...

26:48.640 --> 26:50.574
with Jean-Jaques.

26:50.642 --> 26:54.203
And Dickie would play
"My Funny Valentine."

26:54.279 --> 26:59.615
It was only later that I found out
he only knows about six songs.

26:59.684 --> 27:02.016
Anyway, I looked forward
to seeing him, I suppose.

27:02.086 --> 27:05.385
[ Speaking Italian ]

27:23.308 --> 27:25.674
[ Men Chattering In Italian ]

27:28.413 --> 27:32.110
Hey, hey, Signor Greenleaf !

27:32.183 --> 27:35.846
You're not at my place by 7.:00,
Tom and I are running off together.

27:35.920 --> 27:38.718
- Okay, fine.
- [ Man ] Oh, Dickie!

27:42.260 --> 27:44.854
## [ Indistinct ]

27:49.033 --> 27:51.558
Oh, hold on.
Hold on.

27:51.636 --> 27:55.902
# Silvana, Silvana #

27:55.974 --> 27:57.908
# You make me smile #

27:57.976 --> 28:01.104
I need
to talk to you.

28:01.179 --> 28:04.114
## [ Continues ]

28:07.151 --> 28:10.382
- [ Dickie ] You're breaking my ribs !
- What ?

28:11.923 --> 28:14.756
You're breaking my ribs !

28:16.561 --> 28:19.758
# But don't #

28:19.831 --> 28:23.460
# Change a hair for me #

28:26.270 --> 28:28.295
# Not if you care #

28:28.373 --> 28:30.671
# For me #

28:32.877 --> 28:37.541
# Stay, little Valentine #

28:38.916 --> 28:42.352
# Stay #

28:46.758 --> 28:48.726
# Each day #

28:48.793 --> 28:56.165
# Is Valentine's Day ##

28:59.852 --> 29:01.410
Ohh !
[ Kisses ]

29:01.487 --> 29:06.447
I could fuck this icebox,
I love it so much.

29:08.227 --> 29:11.754
So, what did you actually
do in New York ?

29:11.831 --> 29:14.595
Played piano in a few places.
I told you.

29:14.667 --> 29:17.727
Well, that's one job.
You told me a lot of jobs.

29:17.803 --> 29:20.294
Few places.
That's a few jobs.

29:20.372 --> 29:22.431
The mysterious Mr. Ripley.

29:22.508 --> 29:25.375
Marge and I spend
hours speculating.

29:25.444 --> 29:28.709
Anyway, I don't even want
to think about New York.

29:28.781 --> 29:31.306
Are you ready ?

29:31.383 --> 29:35.581
- Cold beer. Thank you, Dad.
- Okay.

29:35.654 --> 29:37.747
Copy out from here.

29:39.391 --> 29:42.690
- You bring this with you to Europe ?
- You gonna write something ?

29:42.761 --> 29:45.992
I love the fact that you brought
Shakespeare with you but no clothes.

29:46.065 --> 29:49.466
Ermalinda says you wash out the same
shirt every night. Is that true ?

29:49.535 --> 29:51.469
No. I have more
than one shirt.

29:51.537 --> 29:53.732
She can do that for you.

29:53.806 --> 29:56.434
Anyway, just wear
some of my stuff.

29:56.509 --> 29:58.943
Wear anything you want.
Most of it's ancient.

30:01.146 --> 30:03.239
Now your signature.

30:06.085 --> 30:09.077
Not Dickie.
Your signature.

30:19.932 --> 30:22.025
Without the glasses,
you're not even ugly.

30:24.403 --> 30:27.429
I don't need them
because I never read.

30:28.574 --> 30:31.304
- How do I look ?
- Like Clark Kent.

30:33.913 --> 30:37.144
- Now Superman.
- Superman.

30:41.754 --> 30:44.222
- Okay.
- I know.

30:44.290 --> 30:49.125
It's like a kid's. See this, the "S"
and the "T" ? Fine, vulnerable.

30:49.194 --> 30:52.220
That's pain.
That's secret pain.

30:52.298 --> 30:55.199
Well, that must be a very deep secret,
'cause I don't know about it.

30:55.267 --> 30:58.566
Hmm. There's nothing more
naked than your handwriting.

30:58.637 --> 31:01.367
See how nothing's
quite touching the line ?

31:01.440 --> 31:04.932
- That's vanity.
- Well, we certainly know that's true.

31:10.616 --> 31:13.608
[ Dickie ]
Do you have any brothers ?

31:13.686 --> 31:16.621
No.

31:16.689 --> 31:18.816
No brothers,
no sisters.

31:21.060 --> 31:23.528
Me neither.

31:23.596 --> 31:25.757
Nor does Marge.

31:27.399 --> 31:30.129
All only children.

31:36.141 --> 31:38.268
What does that mean ?

31:40.479 --> 31:42.947
Means we've never
shared a bath.

31:46.919 --> 31:49.854
And I'm cold.
Can I get in ?

31:55.094 --> 31:57.756
No.

32:00.966 --> 32:03.696
I didn't mean
with you in it.

32:07.506 --> 32:11.135
Okay.

32:11.210 --> 32:14.839
Get in. I'm like
a prune anyway.

32:36.568 --> 32:38.627
It is me.
It's an old picture.

32:38.704 --> 32:42.731
Every time ! "Is it you ?
It doesn't look like you."

32:42.808 --> 32:44.673
God !

32:44.743 --> 32:47.541
Letters-- Greenleaf
and for Ripley.

32:47.613 --> 32:50.548
Ooh. Fran. "I miss you.
When are you coming home ?

32:50.616 --> 32:53.176
Stop telling me what
an incredible time you're having.

32:53.252 --> 32:55.345
- How much you love Dickie.
- Whoo !

32:55.421 --> 32:58.549
And Marge
and Mongibello."

32:58.624 --> 33:00.615
And this one, I think,
is from your father.

33:00.693 --> 33:04.356
## [ Dickie Vocalizing.: Jazz ]

33:04.430 --> 33:09.458
- Let me see it. What does he say ?
- He's getting impatient.

33:09.535 --> 33:13.972
He wants me to reassure him that you're
going to be home by Thanksgiving.

33:14.039 --> 33:16.872
You've got to get
a new jacket. Really.

33:16.942 --> 33:19.137
You must be sick
of wearing the same clothes.

33:19.211 --> 33:22.180
I can't. I can't keep spending
your father's money.

33:22.247 --> 33:25.182
I love how
responsible you are.

33:25.250 --> 33:28.378
My dad should make you
chief accountant or something.

33:28.454 --> 33:31.423
Or when I take over,
which is never, I will.

33:31.490 --> 33:35.187
Okay. When you take over,
which is never, I'll accept.

33:35.260 --> 33:37.421
Let me buy you a jacket. When we
get to Rome, there's a great place--

33:37.496 --> 33:41.125
- Battistoni.
- Battistoni.

33:41.200 --> 33:44.863
## [ Italian ]

33:44.937 --> 33:48.100
# Roma, we're taking Tom
to Roma #

33:48.173 --> 33:51.574
# We're going to a-Roma #

33:51.643 --> 33:54.578
[ Chattering In Italian ]

33:59.351 --> 34:02.149
Buon giorno.
Nice sweater.

34:02.221 --> 34:04.280
Where do we get
a carrozza for the Forum ?

34:04.356 --> 34:06.586
- Can we just hire any of them ?
- Relax.

34:06.658 --> 34:09.320
Relax !

34:09.394 --> 34:12.192
It's just there's so much
to do in a single day.

34:12.264 --> 34:16.223
The most important question is where to
eat. I hope Freddie made a reservation.

34:16.301 --> 34:18.235
Freddie ?

34:18.303 --> 34:21.602
Freddie.
Freddie Miles.

34:21.673 --> 34:24.005
Freddie's organizing
the Cortina skiing trip.

34:24.076 --> 34:25.805
Oh.

34:25.878 --> 34:28.438
Oh, here he is.

34:28.514 --> 34:30.709
[ Tires Screech ]

34:31.884 --> 34:34.079
- Frederico !
- Come stai ?

34:34.153 --> 34:36.815
- [ Italian ]
- [ Italian ]

34:39.558 --> 34:43.085
Oh, God, don't you want to fuck
every woman you see just once ?

34:43.162 --> 34:46.359
- Only once ?
- Absolutely. Once. Ciao.

34:46.431 --> 34:48.365
- Tom Ripley, Freddie Miles.
- Tom.

34:48.433 --> 34:53.564
I mean, hey, if I'm late,
think what her husband's saying.

34:53.639 --> 34:56.301
- You look gorgeous.
- As always.

34:57.442 --> 34:59.376
So, mangiare.

34:59.444 --> 35:01.776
Si. I got us a table
outside at Fabrizio's. Tommy.

35:01.847 --> 35:03.815
[ Dickie ]
Outstanding. I tell you,

35:03.882 --> 35:06.680
- I'm so cabin-crazy with Mongi.
- I know. I was there.

35:06.752 --> 35:08.947
## [Jazz ]

35:22.234 --> 35:25.362
Look, Tom, we got to go to a club
and meet some friends of Freddie's.

35:25.437 --> 35:28.804
The best thing is, if you want
to be a tourist, grab a cab now,

35:28.874 --> 35:31.570
and I'll meet you
at the railway station.

35:31.643 --> 35:33.577
What club ?

35:35.247 --> 35:38.739
Freddie's arranged it
with some of the skiing crowd.

35:40.219 --> 35:42.483
Come if you want, but I thought
you wanted to go sightseeing.

35:42.554 --> 35:45.546
I do, and then maybe get the jacket
and what have you.

35:45.624 --> 35:47.888
Dick !
You gotta hear this.

35:49.127 --> 35:51.994
Listen, just take
one of mine when we get back.

35:52.064 --> 35:54.692
Don't worry about it.

35:56.568 --> 35:58.502
Come on !

36:08.647 --> 36:11.115
Ciao.
Have fun, okay ?

36:19.224 --> 36:21.488
[ Knocking ]

36:23.795 --> 36:27.231
You said to make sure you didn't
miss the train. Leaves at 8:00.

36:27.299 --> 36:29.233
[ Snickers ]

36:29.301 --> 36:31.360
Have a good time.

36:31.436 --> 36:33.165
See ya, Tommy.

36:39.611 --> 36:41.977
## [ Whistles ]

