37:27.883 --> 37:30.613
# I'd sing to her #

37:31.687 --> 37:34.815
# May I be the only one #

37:34.890 --> 37:37.358
# To say I #

37:37.426 --> 37:41.726
# Really fell in love
the day I #

37:41.797 --> 37:45.130
# First set eyes on you #

37:47.536 --> 37:50.937
- # May I ##
- What are you doing ?

37:51.006 --> 37:53.702
Oh. I was just
amusing myself.

37:54.977 --> 37:59.311
- Sorry.
- I wish you'd get out of my clothes.

37:59.381 --> 38:03.977
- Do you have my shoes on too ?
- You said I could pick out a jacket--

38:07.022 --> 38:08.990
Did you get undressed
in your own room ?

38:11.860 --> 38:14.124
Thought you missed
the train.

38:14.196 --> 38:16.790
Freddie drove me back
in his car.

38:16.865 --> 38:19.857
- Is Freddie here ?
- He's downstairs.

38:19.935 --> 38:23.098
I was just fooling around.

38:23.171 --> 38:27.164
Don't say anything.
I was just fooling around.

38:28.877 --> 38:30.811
Sorry.

38:32.781 --> 38:35.215
[ Freddie ]
God. A corduroy jacket in Italy.

38:35.284 --> 38:37.218
- [ Marge ] Good morning, Tom.
- Morning.

38:37.286 --> 38:40.016
- [ Chuckles ]
- Come join us.

38:41.924 --> 38:45.917
Hey. I want this job
of yours, Tommy.

38:45.994 --> 38:48.929
I was just saying,
you live in Italy,

38:48.997 --> 38:52.558
you stay at Dickie's house,
you eat Dickie's food,

38:52.634 --> 38:57.503
you wear his clothes,
and his father picks up the tab.

38:57.573 --> 39:01.031
[ Chuckles ]
If you get bored,

39:01.109 --> 39:04.601
you let me know,
'cause I'll do it.

39:04.680 --> 39:07.547
- I'll do it.
- [ Dickie ] To the mainland!

39:11.587 --> 39:14.818
You really should go in.
It's marvellous.

39:14.890 --> 39:17.984
I'm fine.

39:18.060 --> 39:20.221
[ Dickie Shouting ]

39:27.536 --> 39:29.561
Are you okay ?

39:30.639 --> 39:32.732
Sure.

39:36.878 --> 39:39.608
The thing with Dickie--

39:39.681 --> 39:44.709
It's like the sun shines
on you, and it's glorious.

39:46.188 --> 39:49.749
And then he forgets you
and it's very, very cold.

39:49.825 --> 39:51.759
So I'm learning.

39:51.827 --> 39:55.319
When you have his attention, you feel
you're the only person in the world.

39:55.397 --> 39:58.127
That's why
everybody loves him.

39:58.200 --> 40:01.931
It's always the same. Whenever
someone new comes into his life--

40:02.004 --> 40:04.564
Freddie, Fausto,
Peter Smith-Kingsley.

40:04.640 --> 40:06.972
He's wonderful.
Have you met him ?

40:09.478 --> 40:11.912
Especially you.

40:16.451 --> 40:19.215
And that's just the boys.

40:24.292 --> 40:26.317
[ Dickie,
Freddie Shouting ]

40:26.395 --> 40:29.660
Come get him !
Come get him !

40:29.731 --> 40:31.665
Tell me, why is it
that when men play,

40:31.733 --> 40:34.293
they always play
at killing each other ?

40:34.369 --> 40:37.497
[ Dickie ] He's drowning me!
He's drowning me!

40:39.474 --> 40:43.342
- I'm sorry about Cortina, by the way.
- What about Cortina ?

40:45.814 --> 40:48.681
Didn't--
Didn't-Didn't Dick say ?

40:50.385 --> 40:53.320
[ Sighs ] He spoke to Freddie,
and-and apparently...

40:53.388 --> 40:55.322
it's not going
to work out.

40:57.092 --> 40:59.526
It's because
everyone else can ski,

40:59.594 --> 41:01.858
and it affects
where you stay, and--

41:09.304 --> 41:11.795
[ Dickie ]
Come on, Freddie.

41:11.873 --> 41:14.467
At least stick around for
the Festival of the Madonna.

41:14.543 --> 41:17.137
- The whole town comes out--
- I don't think so.

41:17.212 --> 41:21.876
I have my own, uh, Madonna back in Rome.
Why don't you come back with me ?

41:21.950 --> 41:24.475
A lot of ladies.
Ooh.

41:24.553 --> 41:26.817
[ Chuckles ]

41:30.125 --> 41:32.320
- Oh, God.
- You want to take over ?

41:32.394 --> 41:34.328
Yeah, sure.

41:34.396 --> 41:37.331
Just point her at Capri.
Avoid the rocks.

41:37.399 --> 41:39.867
Where are you going ?

41:39.935 --> 41:41.926
Marge maintenance.

41:42.003 --> 41:43.937
Aye-aye.

41:59.554 --> 42:05.015
[ Marge, Dickie Murmuring ]

42:05.093 --> 42:07.027
[ Marge ]
Don't.

42:15.003 --> 42:17.836
[ Scoffs ]

42:20.642 --> 42:22.701
- [ Marge ] Dickie--
- [ Dickie Moaning ]

42:24.780 --> 42:28.546
Tommy.
How's the peeping ?

42:29.684 --> 42:33.882
Tommy,
how's the peeping ?

42:35.824 --> 42:38.000
Tommy, Tommy,
Tommy, Tommy, Tommy.

42:57.787 --> 43:00.779
## [ Chanting, Indistinct ]

43:04.660 --> 43:07.857
[ People Applauding ]

43:12.535 --> 43:15.561
## [ Chanting Continues ]

43:35.424 --> 43:37.915
## [ Chanting Continues ]

43:55.611 --> 43:58.546
[ Screaming In Italian ]

44:01.017 --> 44:03.508
[ People Shouting ]

44:30.012 --> 44:32.003
Is someone getting
an ambulance ?

44:36.819 --> 44:40.255
- Is someone getting an ambulance ?
- [ Wailing ]

44:46.562 --> 44:49.588
[ People Chanting ]

44:55.171 --> 44:58.072
[ Chanting Continues ]

45:00.176 --> 45:02.736
[ Shouting, Indistinct ]

45:08.842 --> 45:11.743
What's the fight about ?
That's her fiance, isn't it ?

45:11.812 --> 45:16.681
- I don't know. Why are you asking me ?
- Are they blaming him ?

45:16.750 --> 45:20.413
How can it take an hour
to find an ambulance ?

45:20.487 --> 45:23.012
She was already dead, darling,
wasn't she ? So I suppose--

45:23.089 --> 45:27.583
I don't know why people say
this country is civilized.

45:27.661 --> 45:30.789
- Dickie !
- It isn't. It's fucking primitive.

45:32.432 --> 45:34.832
I'll go see
what's the matter.

45:34.901 --> 45:36.835
I'll go.

45:41.608 --> 45:44.076
## [ Saxophone ]

45:53.420 --> 45:55.388
[ Tom ]
I know why you're upset.

45:58.058 --> 46:00.618
I know about
Silvana, Dickie.

46:03.330 --> 46:05.457
I know about
you and Silvana.

46:05.532 --> 46:08.023
What about us ?

46:11.171 --> 46:14.732
You don't have
to clean up ! Really !

46:22.449 --> 46:25.179
- Like what ?
- Forget it.

46:27.320 --> 46:29.754
She was pregnant.
Did you know that ?

46:34.327 --> 46:37.387
Silvana was pregnant.

46:38.698 --> 46:41.292
Do you know what that means
in a place like this ?

46:41.368 --> 46:44.303
I'm prepared
to take the blame.

46:44.371 --> 46:48.273
- What are you talking about ?
- You've been so good to me.

46:48.341 --> 46:53.074
You're the brother I never had.
I'm the brother you never had.

46:53.146 --> 46:55.876
I would do anything
for you, Dickie.

46:58.184 --> 47:00.277
She came to me for help.

47:00.353 --> 47:02.480
She needed money.

47:05.492 --> 47:09.929
I didn't help her.
I didn't help her.

47:09.996 --> 47:14.330
Now she's drowned herself,
and it's my fault.

47:21.641 --> 47:23.575
I'm not going
to say anything--

47:23.643 --> 47:26.771
to Marge, to the police
or anybody.

47:26.846 --> 47:29.872
It's a secret
between us, Dickie.

47:32.052 --> 47:33.986
And I'll keep it.

47:35.555 --> 47:38.080
[ Tom Reading ] "Dear Tom.
In view of the fact Dickie shows...

47:38.158 --> 47:42.959
no more signs of coming home than
before you went--" blah, blah, blah--

47:43.029 --> 47:45.793
Um--

47:45.865 --> 47:48.493
"I hope that the trip has
afforded you some pleasure...

47:48.568 --> 47:51.765
despite the failure
of its main objective.

47:51.838 --> 47:56.332
You no longer should consider yourself
obligated to us in any way."

47:56.409 --> 47:58.400
Can't blame him.

47:58.478 --> 48:00.571
You could hardly expect this
to go on forever, Tom.

48:00.647 --> 48:03.138
Well, you can write again.

48:03.216 --> 48:06.117
- Especially now we're brothers.
- I can't.

48:06.186 --> 48:08.313
How can I,
in all decency.

48:08.388 --> 48:11.118
You said it yourself.
It's my dad's money you're spending.

48:11.191 --> 48:15.321
We've had a great run
though, haven't we ?

48:15.395 --> 48:19.331
Well, we'll still go to Venice.
We could stick to that plan.

48:19.399 --> 48:21.458
I don't think so, Tom.

48:21.534 --> 48:24.128
You can't pay
your own way, can you ?

48:24.204 --> 48:28.607
It's time we all moved on.

48:28.675 --> 48:32.907
I'm sick of Mongi.
Especially now, with everything--

48:32.979 --> 48:34.947
I really want to move
to the north.

48:35.015 --> 48:37.540
I need to check out
San Remo next week.

48:37.617 --> 48:39.642
Find somewhere new
to keep the boat.

48:39.719 --> 48:43.120
It would be great, though,
if you came with me to San Remo.

48:43.189 --> 48:46.681
There's a great jazz festival.
We could say good-bye in style.

48:46.760 --> 48:49.320
What do you think ?

48:49.396 --> 48:52.160
Our last trip !

48:57.737 --> 48:59.671
Sure.

49:35.275 --> 49:37.641
[ Speaking Italian ]

49:53.993 --> 49:56.257
Why do you do
that thing with your neck ?

49:56.329 --> 49:58.263
What thing ?

50:00.433 --> 50:03.834
On trains, you always
do that thing.

50:07.874 --> 50:10.741
Spooky.

50:10.810 --> 50:14.644
Spook-- k-k--
k-k-- k-k--

50:14.714 --> 50:17.512
## [ Imitating
Jazz Percussion ]

50:18.718 --> 50:20.652
Spooky.

50:20.720 --> 50:22.847
## [ Cymbals ]

50:24.924 --> 50:27.290
## [ Jazz ]

50:41.708 --> 50:43.642
Oh !

50:43.710 --> 50:47.476
Didn't I tell you
San Remo was crazy ?

50:47.547 --> 50:50.345
This is more like it !
Come on !

50:53.586 --> 50:55.213
## [ Ends ]

51:00.226 --> 51:02.717
Grazie.

51:02.796 --> 51:05.959
To Mongibello
and the happiest days of my life.

51:06.032 --> 51:08.626
To Mongi.
You're cheerful tonight.

51:08.701 --> 51:11.135
I'm suddenly quite happy
to be going back.

51:11.204 --> 51:13.968
Did I know you
at Princeton, Tom ?

51:14.040 --> 51:16.736
I don't think I did,
did I ?

51:16.810 --> 51:19.973
- Why are you asking all of a sudden ?
- No reason.

51:20.046 --> 51:23.607
Because you're leaving, I guess.
I don't think you were there.

51:24.751 --> 51:27.879
- Why ?
- I mean it as a compliment.

51:27.954 --> 51:29.888
You've got
such great taste.

51:29.956 --> 51:34.120
Most of the thugs at Princeton
had tasted everything and had no taste.

51:34.194 --> 51:39.222
I used to say,
"the cream of America: Rich and thick."

51:39.299 --> 51:41.392
Freddie's
the perfect example.

51:41.467 --> 51:44.061
Then I'll take it
as a compliment.

51:44.137 --> 51:46.105
I knew it !
I knew it.

51:46.172 --> 51:49.039
Marge and I had a bet.

51:57.383 --> 51:59.283
Do you even like jazz,

51:59.352 --> 52:01.592
or was that
for my benefit ?

52:01.726 --> 52:04.388
- I've gotten to like it.
- Oh, yes !

52:06.064 --> 52:08.965
I've gotten to like everything
about the way you live.

52:09.033 --> 52:11.263
It's one big love affair.

52:13.404 --> 52:15.531
If you knew my life
back home in New York--

52:15.606 --> 52:17.699
I'm thinkin'
of givin' up the sax.

52:17.775 --> 52:19.902
What do you think
about the drums ?

52:19.977 --> 52:23.208
- What ?
- So cool.

52:23.281 --> 52:26.182
I'm gonna rent a boat tomorrow,
take a look around.

52:27.251 --> 52:29.811
This is how I found
my place in Mongi.

52:29.887 --> 52:32.913
Took a boat out...

52:32.990 --> 52:34.981
around the bay,

52:35.059 --> 52:37.619
first thing I liked,

52:37.695 --> 52:39.629
I got it.

52:40.998 --> 52:45.264
- Whoa !
- Come on, Dickie. Don't go crazy.

52:45.336 --> 52:47.827
- Dickie. Slow down !
- [ Laughing ] Hold on.

52:47.905 --> 52:49.896
Wait a minute !
It's gonna tip ! Oh, God !

52:49.974 --> 52:53.501
Stop it ! Somebody !
Somebody ! Stop it !

52:53.578 --> 52:56.979
[ Shouting ]

52:57.048 --> 52:59.209
Oh, I love it here !

52:59.283 --> 53:01.808
I love it here !
I'm gonna move here !

53:01.886 --> 53:04.480
Beautiful.

53:06.424 --> 53:08.824
## [ Imitating Cymbal
Percussion ]

53:08.893 --> 53:11.987
I want to tell you
my plan.

53:12.063 --> 53:14.964
- So tell me.
- Well, I thought...

53:15.032 --> 53:17.933
I'd come back in the new year
under my own steam.

53:18.002 --> 53:21.165
- Really ? To Italy ?
- Of course.

53:21.239 --> 53:24.731
And I figured,
just for argument's sake,

53:24.809 --> 53:26.834
say I got a place.

53:26.911 --> 53:29.379
Or say we split
the rent on a house,

53:29.447 --> 53:31.677
I could get a job,
or, better still,

53:31.749 --> 53:33.614
if I got a place in Rome,
and then when we're there,

53:33.684 --> 53:36.482
we could be there, and when we're here,
we could be here.

53:36.554 --> 53:41.116
- I don't think so.
- Particularly with the Marge problem.

53:41.192 --> 53:43.251
You just blame me.

53:44.495 --> 53:48.932
- Marge and I are getting married.
- How ?

53:49.000 --> 53:52.959
- How ?
- Yesterday, you were ogling girls.

53:53.037 --> 53:54.971
Today you're getting married ?
That's absurd.

53:57.041 --> 54:01.000
- I love Marge.
- You love me. You're not marrying me.

54:01.078 --> 54:03.842
- Tom, I don't love you.
- No, I don't mean that as a threat.

54:03.915 --> 54:07.009
To be honest, I'm-I'm a little
relieved you're going.

54:07.084 --> 54:09.848
I think we've seen enough
of each other for a while.

54:14.692 --> 54:17.593
- What ?
- You can be a leech !

54:17.662 --> 54:19.596
You know that !

54:21.666 --> 54:24.794
And... it's boring.

54:27.405 --> 54:30.397
You can be quite boring.

54:42.386 --> 54:44.616
The funny thing is,
I'm not pretending...

54:44.689 --> 54:47.157
to be somebody else,
and you are.

54:47.225 --> 54:50.388
-Boring.
-I've been absolutely honest with you...

54:50.461 --> 54:52.395
about my feelings.

54:52.463 --> 54:55.125
- Boring.
- But you-- First of all,

54:55.199 --> 54:57.133
I know there's something.

54:57.201 --> 55:00.170
That evening, when we played chess,
for instance, it was obvious.

55:00.238 --> 55:03.674
- What evening ?
- It's too dangerous for you to take on.

55:03.741 --> 55:05.800
Oh, no, no.
We're brothers.

55:05.877 --> 55:10.576
Hey. And then you do this sordid thing
with Marge-- fucking her...

55:10.648 --> 55:12.479
on the boat, while we
all have to listen,

55:12.550 --> 55:14.518
which was
excruciating.

55:14.585 --> 55:17.748
And you follow your cock around like a--
And now you're getting married.

55:17.822 --> 55:20.154
No, I'm bewildered.
Forgive me.

55:20.224 --> 55:22.658
You're lying to Marge and then
you're getting married to her.

55:22.727 --> 55:27.061
You're knocking up Sylvana, ruining
everybody-- You want to play the sax.

55:27.131 --> 55:29.531
You want to play the drums. Which is it,
Dickie ? What are you actually--

55:31.469 --> 55:35.235
Who are you ? Huh ?
Some third-class mooch ? Who are you ?

55:35.306 --> 55:37.274
Who are you to say
anything to me ?

55:37.341 --> 55:39.901
Who are you
to tell me anything ?

55:39.977 --> 55:43.071
Actually, I really, really do
not want to be on this boat with you.

55:43.147 --> 55:45.581
- I can't move without you moving.
- Shut up. Shut up.

55:45.650 --> 55:49.086
It gives me the creeps.
You give me the creeps.

55:49.153 --> 55:51.121
- You shut up.
- I can't move without "Dickie, Dickie,"

55:51.188 --> 55:53.247
like a little girl
all the time.

55:53.324 --> 55:55.121
Shut up !

55:56.694 --> 55:59.424
Oh, God, Dickie.

55:59.497 --> 56:02.261
- God's sake.
- Oh-- Oh God !

56:04.402 --> 56:06.893
Okay. Okay.

56:06.971 --> 56:09.098
We have to get you-- Okay--
[ Screams ]

56:11.175 --> 56:13.837
I'm gonna kill you !
Kill you !

56:13.911 --> 56:16.880
[ Screaming ]

56:16.948 --> 56:19.246
You're dead !

56:26.157 --> 56:28.955
Stop ! Stop !
Please ! Please !

56:29.026 --> 56:33.087
- [ Screaming ]
- Stop it ! Stop !

56:35.099 --> 56:37.090
- Dickie, let go !
- I'll kill you!

56:42.807 --> 56:46.470
Stop ! Stop !
Stop !

56:46.544 --> 56:49.342
Stop ! Stop !
Stop !

56:49.413 --> 56:51.574
[ Panting ]

58:52.706 --> 58:55.106
Hi. Can I have
my key, please ?

58:55.175 --> 58:57.143
Of course.

58:57.210 --> 59:00.668
You must be very cold.
Uh, Signor Greenleaf, yes ?

59:00.747 --> 59:02.681
No. I'm--

59:41.154 --> 59:43.179
[ Keyboard Clacking ]

1:00:12.418 --> 1:00:15.910
- Hello, Marge.
- [ Screams ]

1:00:15.989 --> 1:00:18.617
Tom !
[ Chuckles ]

1:00:18.691 --> 1:00:20.750
You startled me !

1:00:20.827 --> 1:00:24.024
- Sorry. How are you ?
- You're back!

1:00:24.097 --> 1:00:26.565
- Your book going well?
- Yes.

1:00:26.633 --> 1:00:29.659
I'm on a good streak,
thank you.

1:00:29.736 --> 1:00:33.331
I was just...
Iooking at you. So quiet.

1:00:33.406 --> 1:00:36.341
[ Chuckles ]
Where's Dickie ?

1:00:39.646 --> 1:00:42.672
I think he's planning on staying
in Rome for a few days.

1:00:42.749 --> 1:00:46.515
Rome ? Ahh.
Did he say why ?

1:00:46.586 --> 1:00:49.578
I don't understand Dickie.
Your guess is as good as mine.

1:00:49.656 --> 1:00:51.624
What does that mean ?

1:00:51.691 --> 1:00:56.219
Oh, one day I'm invited skiing,
the next day I'm not.

1:00:58.398 --> 1:01:02.664
One day, we're one family,
then the next day he wants to be alone.

1:01:02.735 --> 1:01:04.669
You tell me.

1:01:04.737 --> 1:01:07.297
Is that what he said ?
He wants to be alone ?

1:01:07.373 --> 1:01:11.810
He was thinking of you.
He asked me to deliver this.

1:01:11.878 --> 1:01:15.245
Thank you.
[ Chuckles ]

1:01:15.315 --> 1:01:17.374
He knows
I love this.

1:01:19.152 --> 1:01:22.212
- But why it couldn't have waited. L--
- Errand number one.:

1:01:22.288 --> 1:01:24.813
Deliver Marge's perfume.

1:01:24.891 --> 1:01:27.451
Errand number two:

1:01:27.527 --> 1:01:30.724
Pack some clothes
and his precious saxophone.

1:01:32.365 --> 1:01:34.333
How long is he staying for ?

1:01:34.400 --> 1:01:37.836
Search me.
I guess we're abandoned.

1:02:04.197 --> 1:02:06.563
Goddamn it !

1:02:07.934 --> 1:02:09.868
[ Tom ]
Are you okay?

1:02:20.413 --> 1:02:23.746
There was a letter from Dickie
in with my perfume.

1:02:25.852 --> 1:02:29.515
You realize it's more
than just a few days.

1:02:29.589 --> 1:02:33.582
He's thinking of moving to Rome.
[ Sniffles ]

1:02:33.660 --> 1:02:36.060
The thing is,

1:02:36.129 --> 1:02:38.825
the night before
he left, we--

1:02:38.898 --> 1:02:40.991
we talked about
moving together...

1:02:42.702 --> 1:02:44.795
somewhere north,
and I suppose I...

1:02:47.407 --> 1:02:50.672
put some pressure on him
about getting married.

1:02:52.679 --> 1:02:54.840
I just--
[ Sobs ]

1:02:56.849 --> 1:02:59.147
I just might have
scared him off.

1:03:04.791 --> 1:03:07.453
There's a side to him...

1:03:07.527 --> 1:03:10.860
when our heads
are on the pillow...

1:03:10.930 --> 1:03:14.297
I know no one else sees
that's so tender.

1:03:16.336 --> 1:03:19.669
I think I should come with you
to Rome and confront him.

1:03:25.979 --> 1:03:28.880
He hates
being confronted.

1:03:30.650 --> 1:03:32.891
I think you're right.

1:03:41.834 --> 1:03:43.995
Grazie.
Checking in.

1:03:52.411 --> 1:03:54.345
Checking in.

1:03:54.413 --> 1:03:58.543
- Signor Ripley ?
- It's me.

1:04:00.719 --> 1:04:03.813
Signor Greenleaf.

1:04:03.889 --> 1:04:06.380
Of course.
Welcome back.

1:04:06.458 --> 1:04:08.858
Thank you.

1:04:26.311 --> 1:04:28.245
[ Woman ] Pronto ?

1:04:28.313 --> 1:04:31.680
Yes, I'd like to telephone
the Hotel Goldoni.

1:04:31.750 --> 1:04:36.346
- Si, signor.
- I want to speak to Thomas Ripley.

1:04:36.422 --> 1:04:39.357
- Ripley ? Subito.
- Yes. Grazie.

1:04:47.332 --> 1:04:52.326
- [ Phone Buzzes ]
- Pronto.

1:04:52.404 --> 1:04:54.338
Signor Greenleaf,
Signor Ripley's not there.

1:04:54.406 --> 1:04:56.533
- He's not there ?
- No, signor.

1:04:56.608 --> 1:04:59.338
Well, I would like
to leave a message.

1:04:59.411 --> 1:05:01.675
- He's not there ? I'll leave a message.
- No, signor.

1:05:01.747 --> 1:05:03.874
- Got your call.
- Got your call.

1:05:03.949 --> 1:05:05.883
- Dinner tonight...
- Dinner tonight...

1:05:05.951 --> 1:05:07.885
- sounds fine.
- Sounds fine.

1:05:07.953 --> 1:05:11.445
- Ripley. Ripley.
- Ripley.

1:05:11.523 --> 1:05:15.015
- Dickie Greenleaf.
- [ Woman ] Dickie Greenleaf.

1:05:15.094 --> 1:05:18.086
- Yes. Greenleaf.
- Greenleaf.

1:05:18.163 --> 1:05:20.290
At the Grand.

1:05:20.365 --> 1:05:23.801
[ Tom ] And I'd like to have
this wallet embossed.

1:05:23.869 --> 1:05:25.803
I don't know
the word in Italian.

1:05:25.871 --> 1:05:27.896
Embossed. Of course,
Signor Greenleaf.

1:05:27.973 --> 1:05:29.941
Thank you.

1:05:33.679 --> 1:05:37.376
Dickie !
It's--

1:05:40.452 --> 1:05:42.386
- Oh, my gosh.
- Meredith.

1:05:42.454 --> 1:05:44.388
- Ciao !
- Ciao. Come in. Come in.

1:05:44.456 --> 1:05:47.118
But you're going skiing
with those Yankees, aren't you ?

1:05:47.192 --> 1:05:51.856
- What ?
- At Christmas. To Cortina.

1:05:51.930 --> 1:05:53.898
- With Freddie Miles.
- How did you know that ?

1:05:53.966 --> 1:05:57.993
Oh ! Everybody
knows Freddie Miles.

1:06:00.706 --> 1:06:02.697
Is Freddie in Rome ?

1:06:02.775 --> 1:06:04.709
- Now ?
- Yeah.

1:06:04.777 --> 1:06:07.143
Oh, I don't think so.

1:06:07.212 --> 1:06:11.615
But l-- But I've met him,
of course, and we've chatted.

1:06:11.683 --> 1:06:15.312
And I know about you...

1:06:15.387 --> 1:06:17.981
and Marge in Mongi.

1:06:18.056 --> 1:06:21.253
What an unreliable
rat you are.

1:06:21.326 --> 1:06:23.590
Well, Freddie said
you were a rat.

1:06:23.662 --> 1:06:25.960
And I thought
to myself,

1:06:26.031 --> 1:06:29.159
" Ah, now I know why
he travels under 'R.'"

1:06:29.234 --> 1:06:31.566
I've left Marge,
Meredith.

1:06:31.637 --> 1:06:33.867
And Mongi.

1:06:33.939 --> 1:06:37.204
- So the rat's here in Rome.
- Oh, I'm sorry.

1:06:37.276 --> 1:06:40.404
Oh, don't be sorry, no.
I've never been happier.

1:06:40.479 --> 1:06:43.778
L-- I feel like
I've been handed a new life.

1:06:43.849 --> 1:06:47.751
The truth is that if you've had money
your entire life,

1:06:47.820 --> 1:06:51.119
either you despise it,
which we do-- agreed ?

1:06:51.190 --> 1:06:54.159
You're only truly comfortable
around other people...

1:06:54.226 --> 1:06:57.286
who have it
and despise it.

1:06:57.362 --> 1:06:59.296
I know.

1:07:00.799 --> 1:07:03.427
I've never admitted that
to anyone.

1:07:06.071 --> 1:07:08.904
[ Chattering In Italian ]

1:07:08.974 --> 1:07:12.239
[ Meredith ] Because my friend
Mr. Greenleaf, Signor Greenleaf and I,

1:07:12.311 --> 1:07:14.245
are on a little spending spree.

1:07:14.313 --> 1:07:18.272
- [ Man ] I see.
- We're behaving very badly.

1:07:18.350 --> 1:07:22.810
Oh, I love Italian money. So dark.
Doesn't make you feel guilty.

1:07:22.888 --> 1:07:24.822
- Gr-r-razie.
- Thank you.

1:07:35.400 --> 1:07:38.927
I don't want too many large bills.
No one will change them.

1:07:39.004 --> 1:07:41.097
Tutto bene,
Signor Greenleaf.

1:07:43.709 --> 1:07:47.372
[ Counting In Italian ]

1:07:47.446 --> 1:07:50.813
[ Italian ]

1:07:56.922 --> 1:08:00.585
- I really like this too.
- I think I'm having that too.

1:08:00.659 --> 1:08:02.320
[ Italian ]

1:08:06.932 --> 1:08:09.423
- Tomorrow.
- [ Italian ]

1:08:14.239 --> 1:08:16.730
- Arrivederci.
- Arrivederci. Oops !

1:08:17.943 --> 1:08:19.877
- Ciao.
- Ciao.

1:08:25.384 --> 1:08:29.787
I know you're a jazz fiend,
but do you absolutely hate the opera ?

1:08:33.025 --> 1:08:35.926
I've--
I've...

1:08:35.994 --> 1:08:39.623
been trying to give
my tickets away.

1:08:39.698 --> 1:08:44.135
It's tomorrow. But if
you were prepared to be dragged--

1:08:45.637 --> 1:08:47.832
You could drag me.

1:08:52.077 --> 1:08:54.568
## [ Opera: Italian ]

1:09:42.932 --> 1:09:45.196
[ Shot Fires ]

1:09:45.268 --> 1:09:47.463
[ Body Thuds ]

1:10:30.647 --> 1:10:34.481
[ Audience Applauding ]

1:10:36.119 --> 1:10:39.816
Feodor Chaliapin.
It's the whole Russian baritone.

1:10:39.889 --> 1:10:43.290
Thank you so much
for inviting me tonight.

1:10:43.359 --> 1:10:47.193
Can you bear it ?
We hear you are a friend of Freddie's.

1:10:47.263 --> 1:10:50.460
He has "I hate opera"
tattooed on his chest.

1:10:50.533 --> 1:10:53.024
There's room for a whole
libretto on Freddie's chest.

1:10:55.138 --> 1:10:57.470
I'm sure
we've met before.

1:10:57.540 --> 1:11:00.475
I was sure we'd met before.
Weren't you, Ted ?

1:11:00.543 --> 1:11:02.568
Dick is Herbert
Greenleaf's boy.

1:11:02.645 --> 1:11:05.205
- I know.
- Yes, I think we have.

1:11:05.281 --> 1:11:09.377
One minute you people are children,
and the next you're getting tattooed.

1:11:11.354 --> 1:11:13.914
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

1:11:16.025 --> 1:11:17.959
Cheers.

1:11:22.265 --> 1:11:24.699
- Excuse me.
- Prego.

1:11:24.767 --> 1:11:27.133
Oh !
Excuse me.

1:11:27.203 --> 1:11:29.433
- Hello.
- Hello.

1:11:30.940 --> 1:11:32.874
- Tom !
- Marge !

1:11:32.942 --> 1:11:36.070
How are you ?
What are you doing in Rome ?

1:11:36.145 --> 1:11:39.808
- Is he here ? Are you with Dickie ?
- No. Um, no.

1:11:39.882 --> 1:11:42.942
Um, hello.
Um, I'm Tom Ripley.

1:11:43.019 --> 1:11:45.419
Peter Smith-Kingsley. I've heard
all about you from Marge and Dickie.

1:11:45.488 --> 1:11:48.457
- Ditto.
- No-No glasses.

1:11:48.524 --> 1:11:51.357
So, where are you hiding him ?
He's impossible, isn't he ?

1:11:51.427 --> 1:11:53.554
Is he really not here ?

1:11:53.630 --> 1:11:57.293
Marge, you know Dickie has
"I hate opera" tattooed on his chest.

1:11:57.367 --> 1:12:00.393
- I thought you were going to Venice.
- Yes, what happened with that ?

1:12:00.470 --> 1:12:02.404
I heard you were
desperate to come.

1:12:02.472 --> 1:12:04.463
I was rather looking forward
to rowing you around.

1:12:04.540 --> 1:12:08.237
- [ Bell Ringing ]
- I am. I really am.

1:12:08.311 --> 1:12:11.542
I've been travelling, and I just can't
seem to get that far north.

1:12:11.614 --> 1:12:13.479
Well, you should hurry,
before we sink.

1:12:13.549 --> 1:12:16.643
Look, let me give you
the telephone number.

1:12:16.719 --> 1:12:19.586
There. Oh, look.
There's Meredith.

1:12:19.656 --> 1:12:22.921
Meredith. What's her name,
Marge ? The textile people.

1:12:22.992 --> 1:12:26.484
Um, come on. Some of us
spent Christmas at her house.

1:12:26.562 --> 1:12:30.293
I don't know her.

1:12:30.366 --> 1:12:34.166
He hasn't called.
He's hardly written.

1:12:34.237 --> 1:12:36.364
Just these cryptic
notes, you know ?

1:12:36.439 --> 1:12:38.464
- You don't just dump people.
- [ Bell Rings ]

1:12:38.541 --> 1:12:42.170
Look, will we see you later,
or are you with people ?

1:12:42.245 --> 1:12:45.237
- Uh, I can't later.
- Well, how about tomorrow ?

1:12:45.314 --> 1:12:47.248
Yes, uh,
maybe in the morning ?

1:12:47.316 --> 1:12:50.979
Do you know Cafe Dinelli
at the Piazza di Spagna ?

1:12:51.054 --> 1:12:54.546
- I know the Piazza. What time ?
- 10:30 ?

1:12:54.624 --> 1:12:56.854
- We'll be there.
- Okay.

1:12:56.926 --> 1:12:58.951
So I'll see you
in the morning, Marge ?

1:12:59.028 --> 1:13:02.088
10.:30 ?
Very nice to meet you.

1:13:02.165 --> 1:13:04.224
[ Peter ]
And you.

1:13:07.103 --> 1:13:08.968
Come on.

1:13:09.038 --> 1:13:12.974
Come on.
Let's go back in.

1:13:18.881 --> 1:13:21.975
I don't understand why
Tom's still in Rome.

1:13:22.051 --> 1:13:26.317
- [ Whispering ] Let's go.
- I thought you were enjoying yourself.

1:13:26.389 --> 1:13:28.687
Let's take a carrozza
and look at the moon.

1:13:28.758 --> 1:13:30.692
Are you crazy ?
It's freezing out there.

1:13:30.760 --> 1:13:33.593
Come on. I need to talk to you.
Just the two of us.

1:13:33.663 --> 1:13:35.756
[ Meredith ]
Okay.

1:13:39.535 --> 1:13:42.026
[ Meredith ]
Don't worry, please.

1:13:42.105 --> 1:13:44.972
Don't worry.

1:13:45.041 --> 1:13:49.137
You're such a pal
to understand. L--

1:13:49.212 --> 1:13:51.339
It's like Marge is here
right now. I look at you,

1:13:51.414 --> 1:13:53.507
and I see her face.

1:13:53.583 --> 1:13:56.347
And I can't-- No matter
what I'm feeling towards you--

1:13:56.419 --> 1:14:01.789
No. I absolutely...
understand. Of c--

1:14:01.858 --> 1:14:05.350
Otherwise, you'd be
fighting me off.

1:14:05.428 --> 1:14:07.396
Beating you away.

1:14:46.068 --> 1:14:49.299
But will you meet me
tomorrow ?

1:14:49.372 --> 1:14:52.603
Just to say good-bye properly,
you know, in the daylight,

1:14:52.675 --> 1:14:54.836
so it's not just this.

1:14:54.911 --> 1:14:57.675
Of course. Meredith, I'm sorry.
Of course I'll meet you.

1:14:57.747 --> 1:15:02.980
You should always
save pain for daylight.

1:15:03.052 --> 1:15:06.351
Why don't we have coffee
in the morning at Dinelli's ?

1:15:06.422 --> 1:15:08.583
Uh, by the Spanish Steps.

1:15:08.658 --> 1:15:10.489
Exactly. 10:30 ?

1:15:13.229 --> 1:15:15.823
- 10:15.
- Okay.

1:15:15.898 --> 1:15:18.059
Okay.

1:15:26.509 --> 1:15:30.445
[ Bell Tolling ]

1:15:33.282 --> 1:15:35.147
[ Tolling Continues ]

1:15:45.261 --> 1:15:47.195
[ Italian ]

1:16:03.756 --> 1:16:07.192
[ Chattering, Indistinct ]

1:16:09.294 --> 1:16:11.626
- [ Peter ] Grazie.
- Peter ?

1:16:11.697 --> 1:16:15.224
Hello.
It's Meredith Logue.

1:16:15.300 --> 1:16:17.962
[ Peter ] Of course it is.
Meredith, hello. Sorry.

1:16:18.037 --> 1:16:21.097
- I was half asleep. How are you ?
- How are you ?

1:16:21.173 --> 1:16:23.539
This is Marge Sherwood.
Meredith Logue.

1:16:23.609 --> 1:16:26.635
How do you do ?

1:16:26.712 --> 1:16:30.045
Do join us, won't you ?
We’re just waiting for a friend.

1:16:30.115 --> 1:16:32.845
L-- I won't, actually.
I think there's--

1:16:32.918 --> 1:16:35.512
- Did we see you at the opera last night ?
- Uh--

1:16:35.587 --> 1:16:38.317
Are you waiting for Dickie ?

1:16:38.390 --> 1:16:42.520
Dickie ? Do you-- Do you--
Do you know Dickie ?

1:16:42.594 --> 1:16:45.757
You were at the opera.
Oh, that explains-- Yes, I was there.

1:16:45.831 --> 1:16:49.358
I was there with Dickie.

1:16:50.436 --> 1:16:53.200
[ Exhales ]
I knew it.

1:16:53.272 --> 1:16:55.502
I told you.

1:16:57.576 --> 1:17:02.104
Marge, I don't know you,
so I've got no right to--

1:17:02.181 --> 1:17:05.378
Dickie loves you.
He's-- Well--

1:17:05.451 --> 1:17:08.614
I think you'll find
he's on his way home to you.

1:17:08.687 --> 1:17:12.714
[ Sighs ] Well, how-how-how
would you know that ?

1:17:13.959 --> 1:17:16.519
He... told me everything.

1:17:16.595 --> 1:17:21.532
No, I was supposed to meet him
15 minutes ago, so, uh,

1:17:21.600 --> 1:17:24.034
I'm gonna go now,
I think.

1:17:26.338 --> 1:17:28.397
God, unless he meant us
to meet.

1:17:28.474 --> 1:17:30.669
That'd be a little cruel,
wouldn't it ?

1:17:30.742 --> 1:17:33.142
No, no, we're
meeting another friend.

1:17:33.212 --> 1:17:36.045
- Tom Ripley.
- Do you know Tom Ripley ?

1:17:36.115 --> 1:17:40.950
No, no. I've heard about him,
of course, but I didn't meet him, no.

1:17:41.019 --> 1:17:43.487
- [ Italian ]
- Not for me. No, grazie.

1:17:48.827 --> 1:17:51.762
Hope I didn't
complicate matters.

1:17:51.830 --> 1:17:57.166
God, nothing, nothing...
untoward happened.

1:17:57.236 --> 1:18:01.468
No, there is nothing to prevent you
from welcoming him back,

1:18:01.540 --> 1:18:03.474
from marrying him.

1:18:08.013 --> 1:18:10.743
Good-bye.
I'm happy to put a face to a name.

1:18:10.816 --> 1:18:13.307
Good-bye, Peter.
Please, don't get up.

1:18:33.839 --> 1:18:36.967
[ Marge ] Now I don't know what to
think. Do you think he's coming back ?

1:18:38.577 --> 1:18:41.978
Sorry. Sorry.
Had to renew my papers.

1:18:42.047 --> 1:18:44.379
Never one stamp when they
can make you line up for three.

1:18:44.449 --> 1:18:46.576
- Have you been waiting long ?
- Not at all.

1:18:46.652 --> 1:18:49.382
- Morning, Tom.
- Hi. Sorry.

1:18:49.454 --> 1:18:51.388
You okay ? You look like
you've seen a ghost.

1:18:51.456 --> 1:18:54.152
Dickie was at the opera
last night.

1:18:54.226 --> 1:18:57.559
I don't believe that. Uh--
Wild horses couldn't drag Dickie--

1:18:57.629 --> 1:18:59.927
[ Laughs ] Well, he was there
with someone, you know,

1:18:59.998 --> 1:19:02.489
so I suppose she must
have dragged him.

1:19:02.568 --> 1:19:05.401
It's not fair.

1:19:05.470 --> 1:19:09.634
I think I'm going back to Mongi.
I think Dickie's coming home.

1:19:09.708 --> 1:19:12.336
Really ? L-- Well,
that's just swell.

1:19:12.411 --> 1:19:15.073
No, you know, you're
way ahead of me. Great.

1:19:15.147 --> 1:19:17.115
That was rather moving
when I heard-- I'm sorry.

1:19:17.182 --> 1:19:19.582
Meredith is the American girl
I saw at the opera last night.

1:19:19.651 --> 1:19:23.747
- She's been seeing something of Dickie.
- Oh, my God.

1:19:23.822 --> 1:19:27.280
But the point is,
Dickie-- and we all know this.

1:19:27.359 --> 1:19:31.022
Dickie loves Marge.
And he misses her.

1:19:31.096 --> 1:19:33.860
I feel guilty.
Marge doesn't understand this,

1:19:33.932 --> 1:19:36.799
but whenever Dickie does
something, I feel guilty.

1:19:36.868 --> 1:19:39.166
[ Chuckles ]
As if that makes sense.

1:19:40.939 --> 1:19:44.306
[ Italian ]

1:19:44.376 --> 1:19:46.401
[ Italian ]

1:20:05.631 --> 1:20:08.566
## [ Choir Singing
In Italian ]

1:20:32.591 --> 1:20:34.525
## [ Ends ]

1:20:44.436 --> 1:20:46.370
[ Knocking At Door ]

1:20:55.013 --> 1:20:58.081
- [ Knocking ]
-## [ Piano.: Stops ]

1:21:02.586 --> 1:21:04.520
[ Freddie ]
Dickie.

1:21:06.223 --> 1:21:08.589
- [ Knocking ]
- Dickie, come on. It's me.

1:21:11.027 --> 1:21:12.961
It's Freddie.
Let me in.

1:21:15.999 --> 1:21:17.933
Dickie.

1:21:23.206 --> 1:21:26.039
Hello, Freddie.
It's Tom.

1:21:27.110 --> 1:21:30.045
Um, where's Dickie ?

1:21:30.113 --> 1:21:32.047
How are you ?

1:21:32.115 --> 1:21:35.175
I'm good. Uh, yes, thank you.
He's gone. He went to dinner.

1:21:35.252 --> 1:21:39.621
- He's at Otello's. You know Otello's ?
- No, no, no.

1:21:39.689 --> 1:21:42.487
L-I don't think he's
at dinner at 6:30 P.M.

1:21:42.559 --> 1:21:45.858
If you said he was still at lunch,
maybe I'd believe you.

1:21:45.929 --> 1:21:49.524
You know ? [ Laughs ]
Incredible.

1:21:49.599 --> 1:21:53.535
I mean, the guy just, you know,
disappeared off the face of the earth.

1:21:55.705 --> 1:21:57.639
I guess.

1:21:58.775 --> 1:22:01.835
The landlady,
as far as I could tell--

1:22:01.912 --> 1:22:05.712
The landlady said
he was here right now.

1:22:05.782 --> 1:22:08.012
Search the place.

1:22:08.084 --> 1:22:11.485
L-I just don't-- I don't know why you'd
imagine that Dickie would hide from you.

1:22:11.554 --> 1:22:13.488
Because he's been
hiding from me.

1:22:15.659 --> 1:22:19.493
- What happened at Christmas ?
- What about Christmas ?

1:22:19.562 --> 1:22:22.690
He was supposed to come skiing.
I didn't get a cable...

1:22:22.766 --> 1:22:24.996
or a call or a little note
or a--

1:22:25.068 --> 1:22:29.596
- [ Grunts ]
- Frankly, a fart.

1:22:29.673 --> 1:22:31.937
Well, he's been very involved
with his music.

1:22:32.008 --> 1:22:36.206
Um, I think his theory... is...

1:22:36.279 --> 1:22:40.875
that you have to go into a cocoon,
uh, before you can be a butterfly.

1:22:40.951 --> 1:22:43.511
Which is horseshit.
[ Mutters ]

1:22:43.586 --> 1:22:47.044
You hear him play this thing ?
Well, he can't.

1:22:49.926 --> 1:22:52.019
How did you find him ?

1:22:52.095 --> 1:22:55.087
It's such an out-of-the-way apartment.
Can I fix you a drink ?

1:22:55.165 --> 1:22:58.134
No, thanks.
At the American Express.

1:22:58.201 --> 1:23:01.500
[ Strikes Random Keys ]

1:23:01.571 --> 1:23:04.005
Some kid.
[ Strikes Keys ]

1:23:09.512 --> 1:23:12.447
Are you living here ?

1:23:12.515 --> 1:23:15.609
No, no. I'm staying here
for a few days.

1:23:18.288 --> 1:23:20.950
- But--
- [ Strikes Keys ]

1:23:21.024 --> 1:23:24.721
It's a new piano.
Probably shouldn't--

1:23:24.794 --> 1:23:28.093
[ Striking Keys ]

1:23:29.265 --> 1:23:31.859
- Probably shouldn't--
- [ Strikes Keys ]

1:23:34.804 --> 1:23:38.570
Did this place come furnished ?

1:23:38.641 --> 1:23:41.838
It doesn't
look like Dickie's, uh--

1:23:41.911 --> 1:23:45.005
It's really horrible,
isn't it ?

1:23:46.583 --> 1:23:50.075
It's so, uh, bourgeois.

1:23:59.596 --> 1:24:01.791
Oh, that's a, uh--
You should-- Watch that.

1:24:01.865 --> 1:24:04.993
Excuse--
Excuse me.

1:24:05.068 --> 1:24:07.002
Excuse me.

1:24:10.006 --> 1:24:14.670
In fact, the only thing that looks
like Dickie... is you.

1:24:14.744 --> 1:24:16.769
- Hardly.
- Hmm.

1:24:18.715 --> 1:24:21.445
Have you done something
to your hair ?

1:24:21.518 --> 1:24:23.543
Is there something
you'd like to say, Freddie ?

1:24:23.620 --> 1:24:26.020
- What ?
- You have something you'd like to say ?

1:24:26.089 --> 1:24:28.455
I think I'm saying it.

1:24:29.893 --> 1:24:33.056
Something's going on.

1:24:33.129 --> 1:24:35.962
Either he's converted
to Christianity,

1:24:37.167 --> 1:24:39.101
or there's something else.

1:24:40.537 --> 1:24:42.664
Well, I would suggest you
ask Dickie that yourself.

1:24:42.739 --> 1:24:45.640
Otello's is on della Croce
just off the Corso.

1:24:45.708 --> 1:24:49.200
Is it on della Croce
just off the Corso ?

1:24:51.281 --> 1:24:55.513
Sure. You're
a quick study, aren't you ?

1:24:55.585 --> 1:24:57.519
Last time you didn't know
you ass from your elbow.

1:24:57.587 --> 1:25:00.021
Now you're giving me directions.

1:25:00.090 --> 1:25:03.856
That's not fair. You probably
do know your ass from your elbow.

1:25:06.763 --> 1:25:08.697
I'll see you.

1:25:13.269 --> 1:25:15.703
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

1:25:18.174 --> 1:25:20.768
[ Italian ]

1:25:20.844 --> 1:25:23.438
[ Freddie ]
No Dickie Greenleaf. Thomas Ripley.

1:25:23.513 --> 1:25:26.914
Si.
[ Italian ]

1:25:32.122 --> 1:25:34.113
Ciao, Dickie.

1:25:38.595 --> 1:25:41.063
Dickie doesn't
play the piano.

1:25:42.599 --> 1:25:44.533
[ Freddie ]
Tommy.

1:25:44.601 --> 1:25:46.535
Tommy!

1:25:46.603 --> 1:25:48.537
Tommy!

1:25:50.306 --> 1:25:53.332
[ Freddie Groaning ]

1:26:11.394 --> 1:26:14.363
[ Tom Grunting ]

1:26:22.272 --> 1:26:25.901
[ Man And Woman Chattering ]

1:26:27.076 --> 1:26:29.874
Oh ! [ Laughs ]
You're making me laugh.

1:26:29.946 --> 1:26:33.746
No. You're just so drunk.
Oh. You're just--

1:26:33.816 --> 1:26:37.149
What can you do, eh ?
You should see my other friends.

1:26:37.220 --> 1:26:39.620
- What can you do ?
- [ Italian ]

1:26:39.689 --> 1:26:42.920
Yes.
Such a pig.

1:26:44.427 --> 1:26:46.361
- [ Laughs ]
- [ Italian ]

1:26:46.429 --> 1:26:51.696
[ Imitating Freddie ] Hey, if I'm drunk,
think what her husband's saying.

1:27:39.117 --> 1:27:41.483
- La polizia.
- Dickie Greenleaf?

1:27:41.553 --> 1:27:44.579
- Yes.
- Inspector Roverini.

1:27:44.656 --> 1:27:46.681
- Can we come in ?
- Please.

1:27:54.399 --> 1:27:56.731
It's a terrible shock,
huh ?

1:27:56.801 --> 1:28:00.498
W-What time did Signor Miles
leave yesterday ?

1:28:00.572 --> 1:28:04.599
Oh, um, I can't be certain
exactly. L--

1:28:04.676 --> 1:28:06.610
8:00, 9:00.

1:28:06.678 --> 1:28:09.408
[ Italian ]

1:28:09.481 --> 1:28:13.884
We'd both taken on, uh,
far too many drinks.

1:28:13.952 --> 1:28:18.514
But it was dark. It was certainly dark
when l-- when I walked him to his car.

1:28:18.590 --> 1:28:21.559
So he drove away,
and, uh, you did what ?

1:28:21.626 --> 1:28:24.720
- I went to bed.
- [ Italian ]

1:28:24.796 --> 1:28:29.460
Freddie's a big man, but I'm in trouble
after a couple of drinks.

1:28:29.534 --> 1:28:32.901
I've been suffering all--

1:28:32.971 --> 1:28:35.030
Who found him ?

1:28:35.106 --> 1:28:37.700
[ Italian ]
You understand, I must ask you...

1:28:37.776 --> 1:28:40.336
to stay in Rome,
Signor Greenleaf.

1:28:40.412 --> 1:28:43.745
Yes, if it's gonna help,
certainly.

1:28:43.815 --> 1:28:47.615
So, the doctor, he has to make
the, um--

1:28:47.686 --> 1:28:51.019
- [ Italian ]
- [ Italian ]

1:28:51.089 --> 1:28:54.320
- Post-mortem.
- Yeah, exactly.

1:28:54.392 --> 1:28:57.054
But, you know,
his first conclusion...

1:28:57.128 --> 1:29:02.191
was that Signor Miles was killed
not later than 7:00 yesterday evening.

1:29:02.267 --> 1:29:05.668
Well, he certainly wasn't dead
when he drove away in his car.

1:29:07.772 --> 1:29:09.706
No.

1:29:09.774 --> 1:29:11.708
[ Chattering ]

1:29:27.459 --> 1:29:29.757
[ Italian ]

1:29:35.033 --> 1:29:37.524
[ Italian ]
It's okay.

1:29:37.602 --> 1:29:40.002
- Okay ?
- Si, si.

1:29:50.382 --> 1:29:53.977
- Did he kill Freddie ?
- Marge. When did you get here ?

1:29:54.052 --> 1:29:56.680
Tell me the truth.
Did he kill Freddie ?

1:29:56.755 --> 1:30:00.282
I'd swear he didn't.
Of course he didn't.

1:30:00.358 --> 1:30:04.590
I tried again.
Waiting here, watching for him.

1:30:04.663 --> 1:30:08.258
Instead, it's you.
Whenever I look for Dickie, I find you.

1:30:10.168 --> 1:30:13.160
What happened to your face ?

1:30:13.238 --> 1:30:15.172
Dickie--
Dickie did it.

1:30:15.240 --> 1:30:17.470
- Dickie ?
- My face. There was an argument.

1:30:17.542 --> 1:30:20.238
L-- I said some things
I shouldn't have said and l--

1:30:20.312 --> 1:30:23.941
About you. About the appalling way
he's treating you, all of us.

1:30:24.015 --> 1:30:26.313
And the next thing I know,
he's launched himself at me.

1:30:26.384 --> 1:30:28.511
- Are you getting on ?
- What ?

1:30:28.586 --> 1:30:30.747
Get on.
I'll take you to him.

1:30:55.213 --> 1:30:58.080
[ Italian ]

1:31:10.595 --> 1:31:12.529
[ Engine Stops ]

1:31:15.233 --> 1:31:17.463
- Where does he live ?
- We passed it a few blocks back.

1:31:17.535 --> 1:31:19.969
It's where the police were.
The Palazzo Gioia.

1:31:21.973 --> 1:31:24.942
Look, they don't even know I'm in Rome,
and I'm not gonna incriminate Dickie.

1:31:25.009 --> 1:31:27.034
Well, perhaps
I shouldn't go either.

1:31:27.112 --> 1:31:30.741
No. Well, go if you want to, but just
don't talk to the police about my face.

1:31:30.815 --> 1:31:34.182
If they know he hit me and his temper,
then he could've hit Freddie.

1:31:34.252 --> 1:31:36.243
I'll catch up
with you later.

1:31:40.492 --> 1:31:42.255
[ Engine Starts ]

1:31:54.475 --> 1:31:57.444
[ Italian ]
Signor Greenleaf !

1:31:57.511 --> 1:32:00.105
It's Signor Greenleaf !
Presto, presto !

1:32:00.180 --> 1:32:02.774
[ Shouting In Italian ]

1:32:05.586 --> 1:32:07.781
Open the door !

1:32:07.855 --> 1:32:10.255
Open up !

1:32:10.324 --> 1:32:12.588
- [ Italian ]
- I live here !

1:32:13.761 --> 1:32:15.695
Mr. Greenleaf !

1:32:17.064 --> 1:32:19.259
Can we go up ?
Do you mind ?

1:32:19.333 --> 1:32:21.927
Of course.
What happened to your face ?

1:32:22.002 --> 1:32:25.699
My scooter. I fell off
getting chased by photographers.

1:32:25.773 --> 1:32:29.800
The telephone, the press,
I've been-- I'm feeling hounded.

1:32:29.877 --> 1:32:32.004
Do you think you could
not give out my address ?

1:32:32.079 --> 1:32:36.709
Never. We've had many requests,
and we say no, even to your fiancee.

1:32:36.784 --> 1:32:38.718
I really don't want
to see anybody.

1:32:38.786 --> 1:32:41.550
- Even your fiancee ?
- Even her.

1:32:41.622 --> 1:32:44.591
[ Man Speaking Italian ]

1:32:44.658 --> 1:32:47.855
- What about Thomas Ripley ?
- What about Tom Ripley ?

1:32:49.863 --> 1:32:51.854
You and Signor Ripley went to San Remo.
Is that right ?

1:32:51.932 --> 1:32:55.060
Yes, we-- We went to San Remo.
That was months ago.

1:32:55.135 --> 1:32:57.296
November, I thought.
Was it ?

1:32:57.371 --> 1:33:00.932
- Did you speak to Tom ?
- November 7 is my information.

1:33:01.008 --> 1:33:03.738
I don't remember
the exact date.

1:33:03.811 --> 1:33:08.248
- When did you last see Signor Ripley ?
- A few days ago.

1:33:08.315 --> 1:33:11.910
- Does he stay with you here ?
- No.

1:33:11.985 --> 1:33:14.351
No.

1:33:15.722 --> 1:33:18.691
Here is a pattern.
Two days ago,

1:33:18.759 --> 1:33:21.751
Freddie Miles is dead,
hmm ?

1:33:22.996 --> 1:33:25.464
He leaves your apartment,

1:33:26.533 --> 1:33:29.297
and he's murdered.

1:33:29.369 --> 1:33:34.500
Yesterday, a little boat
is found in San Remo full of rocks.

1:33:34.575 --> 1:33:39.444
And the owner tells the police
it was stolen on November 7.

1:33:39.513 --> 1:33:42.004
We look at hotel records...

1:33:42.082 --> 1:33:44.880
and we see...

1:33:44.952 --> 1:33:48.149
Dickie Greenleaf
is staying in San Remo.

1:33:48.222 --> 1:33:51.988
And then our boatman remembers
two Americans taking a boat.

1:33:52.059 --> 1:33:54.857
That is not a pattern.
That's a coincidence.

1:33:54.928 --> 1:33:56.896
There must be 50 hotels
in San Remo.

1:33:56.964 --> 1:33:59.797
There were probably a hundred people
renting a boat that day.

1:33:59.867 --> 1:34:02.358
Thirty-one people.

1:34:02.436 --> 1:34:04.461
Thirty-one people.

1:34:05.572 --> 1:34:07.506
Thirty-one, yeah.

1:34:07.574 --> 1:34:09.667
[ Italian ]

1:34:09.743 --> 1:34:12.337
- Marge Sherwood.
- That is Miss Sherwood now.

1:34:21.088 --> 1:34:23.113
Let her in.

1:34:23.190 --> 1:34:25.852
Let her in.
What's the difference ? Let her in.

1:34:28.295 --> 1:34:31.731
No ! Actually--
Actually, no.

1:34:31.798 --> 1:34:34.699
I would-- I would
really appreciate it...

1:34:34.768 --> 1:34:37.635
if you would ask Miss Sherwood
to come back later.

1:34:39.640 --> 1:34:42.108
[ Italian ]

1:34:42.175 --> 1:34:45.042
Thank you.

1:34:45.112 --> 1:34:48.707
May I ask you--

1:34:48.782 --> 1:34:52.343
Why would you speak to your friend
and not your fiancee ?

1:34:52.419 --> 1:34:55.752
Well, l--
I think I just said.

1:34:55.822 --> 1:34:59.155
Um, Mr. Ripley was
handling some business for me.

1:34:59.226 --> 1:35:01.854
Nor does Mr. Ripley
want to marry me...

1:35:01.929 --> 1:35:05.956
and ask me every single day
if I'll marry him and when.

1:35:07.134 --> 1:35:09.125
Do you keep a photograph
of Signor Ripley ?

1:35:09.202 --> 1:35:13.070
I'm not in the habit of carrying
around photographs of my male friends.

1:35:14.708 --> 1:35:16.642
Now I think I've upset you.

1:35:16.710 --> 1:35:19.838
Sorry. My English,
perhaps, is coarse.

1:35:19.913 --> 1:35:22.381
It is a little coarse,
yes.

1:35:25.886 --> 1:35:27.820
I'm sorry.

1:35:27.888 --> 1:35:32.882
But you-- No one has seen
Signor Ripley since San Remo.

1:35:32.960 --> 1:35:34.894
- I have.
- You have, yes.

1:35:34.962 --> 1:35:37.692
And so has Miss Sherwood.
Ask her. And, um,

1:35:37.764 --> 1:35:42.895
if I can remember the name
of the hotel he was staying at--

1:35:42.970 --> 1:35:45.996
Um, the Goldoni.
Tom was staying at the Goldoni.

1:35:46.073 --> 1:35:49.474
Goldoni. The Goldoni.
Good, good, but--

1:35:49.543 --> 1:35:52.103
Yes, you are right.

1:35:52.179 --> 1:35:54.443
You are right.
A coincidence.

1:35:54.514 --> 1:35:56.448
[ Siren Wailing, Distant ]

1:35:56.516 --> 1:36:00.111
[ Sighing ] I look forward
to our next meeting.

1:36:00.187 --> 1:36:02.178
Hmm ? When I will be
more careful with my English.

1:36:02.255 --> 1:36:06.521
[ Roverini ] Ah. I have a witness
who thinks they saw two men...

1:36:06.593 --> 1:36:08.527
getting into Mr. Miles’ car.

1:36:08.595 --> 1:36:12.497
And she wants to identify you
in a confronto.

1:36:12.566 --> 1:36:15.057
Line-up. Tomorrow, then ?

1:36:16.570 --> 1:36:18.504
Uh, tomorrow.

1:36:20.173 --> 1:36:22.107
[ Chuckles ]

1:36:26.113 --> 1:36:28.047
- Buon giorno, Miss Sherwood.
- Buon giorno.

1:36:28.115 --> 1:36:32.279
He's in, but I really don't think
he wants to meet anybody.

1:36:39.660 --> 1:36:41.594
[ Knocking ]

1:36:49.670 --> 1:36:51.604
Dick ?

1:36:55.075 --> 1:36:57.236
Dickie ?

1:36:58.779 --> 1:37:00.713
I know you can hear me.

1:37:06.586 --> 1:37:09.487
[ Sighing ]

1:37:09.556 --> 1:37:12.855
I was gonna say that I would count to
three, and if you didn't open the door--

1:37:12.926 --> 1:37:17.192
But I won't count anymore.

1:37:17.264 --> 1:37:19.255
On you.

1:37:21.301 --> 1:37:24.793
I won't count on you
anymore.

1:37:28.275 --> 1:37:33.178
Whatever it is you've done
or haven't done,

1:37:33.246 --> 1:37:35.737
you've broken my heart.

1:37:37.984 --> 1:37:40.418
That's one thing
I know you're guilty of.

1:37:47.994 --> 1:37:50.428
And I don't know why.
[ Sobbing ]

1:37:52.933 --> 1:37:56.334
I don't know why.
I just don't know why.

1:37:58.105 --> 1:38:00.039
[ Footsteps Receding ]

1:38:01.775 --> 1:38:03.766
[ Typewriter Keys Clattering ]

1:38:03.844 --> 1:38:05.971
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

1:38:06.179 --> 1:38:08.409
[ Tom's Voice ]
My dear Tom.

1:38:08.482 --> 1:38:12.009
I'm getting out of this.

1:38:12.085 --> 1:38:15.612
Freddie's death. Silvana.

1:38:15.689 --> 1:38:19.887
I've thought about going to the police,
but I can't do it.

1:38:19.960 --> 1:38:22.326
I can't face it.

1:38:22.395 --> 1:38:24.043
I can't face anything anymore.

1:38:24.043 --> 1:38:25.135
I can't face anything anymore.

1:38:25.211 --> 1:38:27.975
I wish I could give you
the life I took for granted.

1:38:28.047 --> 1:38:30.982
[ Typewriter Bell Dings,
Clattering Continues ]

1:38:31.050 --> 1:38:33.610
You've always understood
what's at the heart of me, Tom.

1:38:33.686 --> 1:38:37.053
Marge never could.

1:38:37.123 --> 1:38:40.524
I suppose that's why
I'm writing this to you,

1:38:40.593 --> 1:38:43.221
the brother I never had.

1:38:43.296 --> 1:38:46.026
The only true friend
I ever had.

1:38:51.704 --> 1:38:53.638
In all kinds of ways,

1:38:53.706 --> 1:38:58.006
you're much more like the son
my father wanted.

1:38:58.077 --> 1:39:01.308
I realize you can
change the people,

1:39:01.381 --> 1:39:03.872
change the scenery,

1:39:03.950 --> 1:39:06.145
but you can't change
your own rotten self.

1:39:08.955 --> 1:39:11.685
Now I can't think what to do
or where to go.

1:39:13.793 --> 1:39:18.355
I'm haunted by everything
I've done and can't undo.

1:39:19.966 --> 1:39:21.900
I'm sorry.

1:39:24.003 --> 1:39:27.370
I've made a mess of being
Dickie Greenleaf, haven't I ?

1:40:31.738 --> 1:40:34.730
Tom !

1:40:36.910 --> 1:40:40.175
I'll see you over there !

1:40:41.381 --> 1:40:43.747
[ Bell Tolling ]

1:40:48.588 --> 1:40:50.886
I'm so sorry to put you
through this, Peter.

1:40:50.957 --> 1:40:54.552
I just can't face going to the police
by myself when my Italian's so rotten.

1:40:54.627 --> 1:40:56.618
Don't be so daft.
It's fine.

1:40:56.696 --> 1:40:59.358
I'm delighted you finally
made it to Venice.

1:40:59.432 --> 1:41:02.060
I'm delighted, contrary to rumor,
that you're still in one piece.

1:41:02.135 --> 1:41:04.126
- What rumor ?
- Oh, you know.

1:41:04.203 --> 1:41:07.639
That Dickie murdered you
and is travelling under your passport.

1:41:07.707 --> 1:41:09.800
I know. It's ridiculous.

1:41:12.712 --> 1:41:14.805
[ Man Shouting In Italian ]

1:41:15.949 --> 1:41:17.883
[ Shouting Continues ]

1:41:17.951 --> 1:41:20.886
[ Phone Ringing ]

1:41:24.657 --> 1:41:26.591
Welcome to Venice.

1:41:26.659 --> 1:41:29.685
God, this place reeks, doesn't it ?
Can you smell it ?

1:41:29.762 --> 1:41:33.630
Anyway, I've got to
the bottom of the delay, finally.

1:41:33.700 --> 1:41:36.635
We're waiting
for someone from Rome.

1:41:36.703 --> 1:41:39.035
What do you mean ?
They've sent for someone from Rome ?

1:41:39.105 --> 1:41:42.233
- Well, yes. That's good, isn't it ?
- No, I thought...

1:41:42.308 --> 1:41:45.675
that didn't happen in Italy,
that each region is separate.

1:41:45.745 --> 1:41:48.179
I was sure that--
I've read that--

1:41:48.247 --> 1:41:51.114
You've read the papers.
You know what a big deal it's been.

1:41:51.184 --> 1:41:54.244
- American tourist murdered.
- Actually, can we not do this now ?

1:41:54.320 --> 1:41:58.381
- The stench really is--
- [ Man Speaking Italian ]

1:42:01.094 --> 1:42:05.190
[ Italian ]

1:42:11.804 --> 1:42:15.604
[ Continues In Italian ]

1:42:15.675 --> 1:42:20.305
He's taken over the case, 'cause they're
annoyed that the previous chap...

1:42:20.380 --> 1:42:23.247
let Dickie disappear
when he was, um,

1:42:23.316 --> 1:42:25.307
the only suspect
in Freddie's murder.

1:42:25.385 --> 1:42:28.286
[ Italian ]

1:42:28.354 --> 1:42:31.619
In Rome,
about three weeks ago.

1:42:31.691 --> 1:42:33.625
I knew that one.

1:42:33.693 --> 1:42:37.754
Um--
[ Italian ]

1:42:37.830 --> 1:42:40.799
[ Italian ]

1:42:40.867 --> 1:42:45.702
Are you a homosexual ?
Interesting non sequitur.

1:42:45.772 --> 1:42:47.797
No.

1:42:47.874 --> 1:42:51.105
- No.
- Oh.

1:42:51.177 --> 1:42:56.080
By the way, um, officially
there are no Italian homosexuals.

1:42:56.149 --> 1:42:58.674
Makes Michelangelo and
Leonardo very inconvenient.

1:42:58.751 --> 1:43:00.446
Eh ?

1:43:00.520 --> 1:43:03.717
Tell him...
I have a fiancee.

1:43:03.790 --> 1:43:06.156
And Dickie has a fiancee.

1:43:06.225 --> 1:43:09.854
And that Freddie Miles
probably had a string of them.

1:43:09.929 --> 1:43:12.329
[ Italian ]

1:43:21.507 --> 1:43:25.409
Mamma mia.
[ Italian ]

1:43:25.478 --> 1:43:28.914
- [ Inspector Laughing ]
- [ Chuckling ]

1:43:28.981 --> 1:43:31.211
- What did he say ?
- He says " so many fiancees."

1:43:31.284 --> 1:43:35.050
[ Italian ]

1:43:36.389 --> 1:43:39.358
He's asking... if you
killed Freddie Miles...

1:43:39.425 --> 1:43:41.359
and then killed Dickie Greenleaf.

1:43:41.427 --> 1:43:45.386
No ! No, I did not kill Freddie Miles
and then kill Dickie Greenleaf.

1:43:45.465 --> 1:43:48.662
Is he accusing me ?
Ask him if he's accusing me.

1:43:48.734 --> 1:43:51.498
The way it works here,
it's better to be less volatile.

1:43:51.571 --> 1:43:53.732
- But it's absurd!
- [ Italian ]

1:43:53.806 --> 1:43:55.740
[ Italian ]

1:44:02.048 --> 1:44:05.984
[ Italian ]

1:44:09.255 --> 1:44:13.715
They found this
in Dickie's place in Rome.

1:44:13.793 --> 1:44:16.353
- You opened this ?
- Of course.

1:44:32.678 --> 1:44:35.511
It's a suicide note.

1:44:39.318 --> 1:44:43.186
You asked me all these questions and you
already read this suicide note ?

1:45:01.541 --> 1:45:03.634
I don't believe that letter.
Do you ?

1:45:03.709 --> 1:45:07.236
Dickie's letter.
Do you believe it ?

1:45:07.313 --> 1:45:09.747
I don't know
what to believe.

1:45:09.815 --> 1:45:14.497
Can you imagine, though, if he did
kill Freddie, what that must be like ?

1:45:14.631 --> 1:45:18.465
Just to wake up every morning.
I mean, how can you ?

1:45:18.535 --> 1:45:22.027
Just wake up and be a person ?
Drink your coffee.

1:45:22.105 --> 1:45:26.508
Well, whatever you do,
however terrible, however hurtful,

1:45:26.576 --> 1:45:29.875
it all makes sense,
doesn't it, in your head.

1:45:29.946 --> 1:45:32.710
You never meet anybody
who thinks they're a bad person.

1:45:32.782 --> 1:45:36.809
No, I know, but you're still tormented.
You must be. You've killed someone.

1:45:36.886 --> 1:45:40.014
Don't you just take the past
and put it in a room in the basement,

1:45:40.090 --> 1:45:42.081
and lock the door
and never go in there ?

1:45:42.158 --> 1:45:45.525
- That's what I do.
- God, yes.

1:45:45.595 --> 1:45:50.225
But, of course, in my case,
it's probably a whole building.

1:45:50.300 --> 1:45:53.326
- ## [ Piano: Stops ]
- And then you meet someone special,

1:45:53.403 --> 1:45:57.464
and all you want to do
is toss them the key.

1:45:58.808 --> 1:46:01.368
Say " Open up. Step inside."

1:46:04.080 --> 1:46:06.310
But you can't...

1:46:06.383 --> 1:46:09.147
- ## [ Resumes ]
- Because it's dark...

1:46:09.219 --> 1:46:12.086
and there are demons.

1:46:13.156 --> 1:46:15.590
And if anybody saw
how ugly it is--

1:46:20.297 --> 1:46:22.356
Now that's the music talking.

1:46:24.634 --> 1:46:27.967
It's harder to be bleak if you're
playing "Knees Up, Mother Brown."

1:46:33.677 --> 1:46:36.646
I keep wanting to do that.

1:46:36.713 --> 1:46:40.581
Fling...
the door open.

1:46:40.650 --> 1:46:42.880
## [ Resumes ]

1:46:42.952 --> 1:46:46.718
Just let the light in,
clean everything out.

1:46:49.025 --> 1:46:53.018
If I could take a giant eraser
and rub out everything,

1:46:53.096 --> 1:46:56.031
starting with myself--

1:46:58.601 --> 1:47:01.832
The thing is, Peter, if--

1:47:04.341 --> 1:47:08.004
- Hmm ?
- If--

1:47:09.846 --> 1:47:11.780
If--

1:47:18.855 --> 1:47:21.187
No key, huh ?

1:47:21.257 --> 1:47:23.953
## [ Boy Singing In Latin ]

1:47:35.905 --> 1:47:38.840
## [ Continues ]

1:48:05.602 --> 1:48:07.593
- Marge.
- Peter.

1:48:10.039 --> 1:48:12.007
- So good to see you.
- Hello, Marge.

1:48:12.075 --> 1:48:14.270
Tom.

1:48:14.344 --> 1:48:18.405
- I see you found Peter.
- I think we sort of found each other.

1:48:18.481 --> 1:48:22.178
- Where's Dickie's father ?
- He's not coming till the morning.

1:48:22.252 --> 1:48:25.813
Evidently his stomach. I don't think
the food here is agreeing with him.

1:48:25.889 --> 1:48:27.823
Oh, I was looking forward
to seeing him.

1:48:27.891 --> 1:48:30.621
Dickie hasn't killed himself.
I'm sure of that.

1:48:30.693 --> 1:48:33.253
There's a private detective
on the case now.

1:48:33.329 --> 1:48:35.820
A Mr. MacCarron
Dickie's father's employed.

1:48:35.899 --> 1:48:39.266
- That's a terrific idea.
- He's American.

1:48:39.335 --> 1:48:42.668
He's already discovered
that Dickie cashed checks for $ 1,000...

1:48:42.739 --> 1:48:44.934
the day before
he disappeared.

1:48:45.008 --> 1:48:46.942
[ Man ]
Signora.

1:48:47.010 --> 1:48:50.446
Is that what you do
before you jump into the Tiber ?

1:48:50.513 --> 1:48:53.107
I don't think so.

1:48:56.920 --> 1:48:59.150
- Is this you ?
- No, it's Tom's.

1:48:59.222 --> 1:49:01.156
Splendid, eh ?

1:49:01.224 --> 1:49:04.557
Golly.
Who's paying for this ?

1:49:04.627 --> 1:49:06.595
Peter found it for me.

1:49:06.663 --> 1:49:11.566
I can afford it because
it's damp and... falling down.

1:49:11.634 --> 1:49:14.797
- Tom's transformed it.
- This is spectacular.

1:49:14.871 --> 1:49:17.135
That's why
Tom wanted you to stay.

1:49:17.207 --> 1:49:19.801
It's better than trying
to squeeze into my room.

1:49:19.876 --> 1:49:21.969
And I know
how you hate hotels.

1:49:22.045 --> 1:49:24.036
A hotel would have been fine.

1:49:27.484 --> 1:49:32.046
We'll have to tell Mr. Greenleaf
how far his dollar stretched.

1:49:35.425 --> 1:49:38.451
- [ Chuckles ]
- What's funny ?

1:49:38.528 --> 1:49:42.055
I was just thinking about when
Tom first came to Mongibello.

1:49:44.100 --> 1:49:47.558
- And look at you now.
- Look at me what ?

1:49:48.838 --> 1:49:50.806
To the manor born.

1:49:52.809 --> 1:49:55.004
[ Bell Tolling ]

1:49:55.078 --> 1:50:04.885
##

1:50:04.954 --> 1:50:07.149
[ Tom ]
Mr. Greenleaf?

1:50:07.223 --> 1:50:10.989
## [ Continues ]

1:50:11.060 --> 1:50:12.994
Mr. Greenleaf?

1:50:13.062 --> 1:50:16.759
Tom. How are you ?
You look well.

1:50:16.833 --> 1:50:19.666
- Thank you, sir. I am well.
- Far cry from New York.

1:50:19.736 --> 1:50:22.227
- Yes, it is.
- Marge.

1:50:22.305 --> 1:50:25.365
Good morning.
Unusual weather.

1:50:25.441 --> 1:50:28.308
- Very.
- And you, sir. Any better ?

1:50:28.378 --> 1:50:31.472
Pretty good.
Sticking with hot water.

1:50:31.548 --> 1:50:33.880
- Where's Mr. MacCarron ?
- San Remo.

1:50:33.950 --> 1:50:36.680
The police are amateurs.

1:50:36.753 --> 1:50:41.281
Well, my boy, it's come
to a pretty pass, hasn't it ?

1:50:41.357 --> 1:50:44.554
What is the detective
hoping to find in San Remo ?

1:50:44.627 --> 1:50:49.462
He's being thorough.
I'm learning about my son, Tom.

1:50:49.532 --> 1:50:52.968
Now he's missing,
I'm learning a great deal about him,

1:50:53.036 --> 1:50:56.130
and I hope that you can
fill in some more blanks for me.

1:50:56.205 --> 1:50:59.265
Marge has been good enough
to do that about Mongibello.

1:50:59.342 --> 1:51:03.142
I'll try my best, sir. Obviously,
I'll do anything to help Dickie.

1:51:03.212 --> 1:51:05.703
-## [ Continues ]
- Good. This theory,

1:51:05.782 --> 1:51:07.909
the letter
he left for you.

1:51:07.984 --> 1:51:11.249
The police think that's
a clear indication...

1:51:11.321 --> 1:51:15.052
he was planning on doing something,
uh, to himself.

1:51:15.124 --> 1:51:17.922
I just don't believe that.

1:51:17.994 --> 1:51:20.519
You don't want to, dear.

1:51:23.733 --> 1:51:25.758
I'd like
to talk to Tom alone.

1:51:25.835 --> 1:51:28.633
Perhaps this afternoon.
Would you mind?

1:51:31.074 --> 1:51:35.101
Marge, what a man may say
to his sweetheart...

1:51:35.178 --> 1:51:37.339
and what he'll admit
to another fellow--

1:51:40.650 --> 1:51:43.346
Such as ?

1:51:43.419 --> 1:51:46.980
## [ Continues ]

1:51:47.056 --> 1:51:50.321
[ Clears Throat ]
What a waste of lives and opportunities.

1:51:50.393 --> 1:51:53.419
I'd pay that fellow a hundred dollars
right now to shut up !

1:52:01.738 --> 1:52:05.105
No, Marge doesn't
know the half of it.

1:52:05.174 --> 1:52:08.439
And his passport photo.

1:52:08.511 --> 1:52:11.394
Did you hear ? To scratch out
his own face like that ?

1:52:11.528 --> 1:52:13.655
Can you imagine ?

1:52:13.730 --> 1:52:16.995
Frame of mind
you'd have to be in ?

1:52:17.067 --> 1:52:20.366
"I've thought about going to the police,
but I can't face it.

1:52:20.437 --> 1:52:23.964
I can't face
anything anymore."

1:52:24.040 --> 1:52:27.373
I feel guilty. I feel
like I pushed him away.

1:52:27.444 --> 1:52:29.503
I feel like I spoke
and he heard you.

1:52:29.579 --> 1:52:32.377
Well,
[ Clears Throat ]

1:52:32.449 --> 1:52:35.043
If we all pushed him away,
what about him pushing us away ?

1:52:35.118 --> 1:52:37.712
You've been a great friend
to my son.

1:52:37.787 --> 1:52:40.915
Everything is
someone else's fault.

1:52:40.991 --> 1:52:43.459
We all want to sow
wild oats,

1:52:43.527 --> 1:52:46.860
but somebody's got to--
got to--

1:52:46.930 --> 1:52:49.728
What is the word ?

1:52:49.799 --> 1:52:52.996
You know, the moment
someone confronts him,

1:52:54.371 --> 1:52:56.896
he lashes out.

1:52:56.973 --> 1:52:59.533
He always has.

1:52:59.609 --> 1:53:03.477
You know, people always say
that you can't choose your parents,

1:53:08.218 --> 1:53:10.709
but you can't choose
your children.

1:53:12.088 --> 1:53:15.649
- [ Knocking ]
- [ Freddie's Voice ] Dickie.

1:53:15.725 --> 1:53:19.320
[ Dickie's Voice ] You can be a leech.
You can be quite boring.

1:53:19.396 --> 1:53:21.330
- [ Tom's Voice ] Stop it!
- [ Dickie's Voice ] It's boring.

1:53:21.398 --> 1:53:25.357
- [ Knocking ]
- [ Voices Overlapping, Indistinct ]

1:53:25.435 --> 1:53:27.767
[ Tom Screaming ]
Stop, stop, stop !

1:53:29.272 --> 1:53:31.172
- Stop, stop, stop !
- [ Freddie's Voice ] Tommy, Tommy.

1:53:31.241 --> 1:53:33.175
[ Dickie's Voice ]
Like a little girl.

1:53:33.243 --> 1:53:36.337
- Like a little girl.
- [ Knocking ]

1:53:36.413 --> 1:53:38.278
[ Knocking ]

1:53:39.983 --> 1:53:41.951
- [ Knocking ]
- Coming.

1:53:42.018 --> 1:53:44.384
- Sorry. I was asleep.
- Finally.

1:53:44.454 --> 1:53:46.581
- I must have fallen asleep.
- Did Dickie's dad go ?

1:53:46.656 --> 1:53:48.590
You look ghastly, Tom.
Did you have a nightmare ?

1:53:48.658 --> 1:53:51.855
- He's having an early night.
- Oh, poor man.

1:53:51.928 --> 1:53:54.419
You know, we were banging
on that door forever.

1:53:58.001 --> 1:53:59.935
[ Marge ]
Uh-oh.

1:54:00.003 --> 1:54:03.598
- I think I've broken a strap.
- Not guilty.

1:54:03.673 --> 1:54:06.642
- I'll fix some drinks.
- [ Marge Giggling ]

1:54:06.710 --> 1:54:09.338
Ah !
You walk in Venice.

1:54:10.880 --> 1:54:12.814
Are you okay ?

1:54:14.284 --> 1:54:16.149
I'm fine.

1:54:16.219 --> 1:54:20.383
- Did you want me to stick around ?
- No, it's okay.

1:54:22.425 --> 1:54:24.620
I could come back.

1:54:39.943 --> 1:54:42.070
Your key.

1:54:45.782 --> 1:54:48.478
- [ Knocking At Door ]
- [ Marge ] Tom ?

1:54:48.551 --> 1:54:52.043
Marge, I'm in the bath.
I won't be long.

1:54:52.122 --> 1:54:54.352
Tom, I have to speak to you.
It's urgent.

1:54:58.094 --> 1:55:00.028
Coming.

1:55:11.541 --> 1:55:14.840
- I found Dickie's rings.
- What ?

1:55:14.911 --> 1:55:16.902
You have Dickie's rings.

1:55:21.685 --> 1:55:23.619
I can explain.

1:55:23.687 --> 1:55:26.383
Dickie promised me he would
never take off this ring.

1:55:26.456 --> 1:55:29.516
Let me put some clothes on
and we'll talk about this.

1:55:29.592 --> 1:55:32.026
- I have to tell Mr. Greenleaf.
- Marge, you're being hysterical.

1:55:32.095 --> 1:55:35.553
He promised me, "I swear, I will never
take off this ring until we get--"

1:55:35.632 --> 1:55:37.566
- Shut up !
- [ Gasping ]

1:55:39.769 --> 1:55:43.227
I'm wet, Marge.
I've lost my towel.

1:55:43.306 --> 1:55:46.298
And I'd really like
to put some clothes on.

1:55:46.376 --> 1:55:48.401
Go and pour us both a drink.

1:55:51.815 --> 1:55:53.749
Pour us a drink.

1:56:27.117 --> 1:56:29.449
Marge ?

1:56:29.519 --> 1:56:31.783
Where are you going ?

1:56:31.855 --> 1:56:35.313
I wasn't snooping.
I just--

1:56:35.392 --> 1:56:38.327
I was looking for a needle
and thread to mend my bra.

1:56:40.330 --> 1:56:43.925
That scent you're wearing.

1:56:44.000 --> 1:56:47.231
I bought that
for you.

1:56:47.303 --> 1:56:49.863
The thing about Dickie--

1:56:49.939 --> 1:56:51.873
So many things.

1:56:53.810 --> 1:56:57.371
That day when he was late
coming back from Rome,

1:56:57.447 --> 1:56:59.381
I tried to tell you this.

1:56:59.449 --> 1:57:02.941
He was with another girl.
I'm not talking about Meredith, either.

1:57:03.019 --> 1:57:06.250
Another girl
that we met in a bar.

1:57:06.322 --> 1:57:09.382
He couldn't be faithful
for five minutes.

1:57:09.459 --> 1:57:11.484
So when he makes a promise,

1:57:11.561 --> 1:57:13.620
it doesn't mean what it means
when you make a promise...

1:57:13.696 --> 1:57:16.256
or I make a promise.

1:57:16.332 --> 1:57:20.325
He has so many realities, Dickie,
and he believes them all.

1:57:20.403 --> 1:57:23.600
He lies. He lies.

1:57:23.673 --> 1:57:28.076
And that's his-- Half the time
he doesn't even realize he's doing it.

1:57:28.144 --> 1:57:31.443
And today,

1:57:31.514 --> 1:57:35.314
I really started wondering whether
he may have killed Freddie.

1:57:35.385 --> 1:57:38.980
He would get so crazy
if anybody would contradict him.

1:57:39.055 --> 1:57:41.751
Well, you know that.
You know that.

1:57:41.825 --> 1:57:44.453
You know that.

1:57:44.527 --> 1:57:46.791
And that's the irony, Marge.

1:57:46.863 --> 1:57:48.797
I loved you.

1:57:48.865 --> 1:57:50.799
You may as well know, Marge.
I loved you.

1:57:50.867 --> 1:57:53.597
I don't know, maybe it's
grotesque of me to say this now,

1:57:53.670 --> 1:57:56.503
so just... write it on a piece
of paper or something...

1:57:56.573 --> 1:57:59.041
and put it in your purse
for a rainy day.

1:57:59.108 --> 1:58:03.340
"Tom loves me. Tom loves me."

1:58:03.413 --> 1:58:05.779
- Why do you have Dickie's rings ?
- I told you.

1:58:05.849 --> 1:58:08.943
- He gave them to me.
- Why ? When ?

1:58:09.018 --> 1:58:12.044
I feel as if you haven't been listening
to anything I've been saying to you.

1:58:12.121 --> 1:58:15.386
I don't believe you.
I don't believe you.

1:58:15.458 --> 1:58:17.790
- It's all true.
- I don't believe...

1:58:17.861 --> 1:58:22.264
a single word you've said.
[ Gasping, Shuddering ]

1:58:22.332 --> 1:58:25.062
You're shivering, Marge.
Look at you.

1:58:25.134 --> 1:58:28.934
Marge, can I hold you ?

1:58:29.005 --> 1:58:30.973
Will you let me hold you ?

1:58:31.040 --> 1:58:33.121
- [ Screaming ]
- Marge ?

1:58:33.255 --> 1:58:36.315
- Peter ! Thank God you're here.
- What's going on ?

1:58:36.391 --> 1:58:39.724
Get me out of here.
Get me out of here. Please!

1:58:39.795 --> 1:58:44.630
- [ Peter ] Tom, are you okay ?
- [ Marge Sobbing ]

1:58:44.700 --> 1:58:47.828
You try.
You try talking to her.

1:58:48.904 --> 1:58:50.997
- [ Peter ] Tom ?
- I give up.

1:58:51.073 --> 1:58:53.667
Tell me what's going on.
Tom !

1:58:53.742 --> 1:58:56.210
- [ Tom ] What did I ever do to her?
- Listen--

1:58:56.278 --> 1:58:59.406
Have her tell you one thing
that I've ever done to her.

1:58:59.481 --> 1:59:02.177
You can't be angry
with her.

1:59:02.251 --> 1:59:05.186
She's confused, and she needs
someone to blame.

1:59:05.254 --> 1:59:07.188
So she blames you.

1:59:07.256 --> 1:59:09.816
I'll go back home
and talk to her.

1:59:09.892 --> 1:59:12.383
As for you,

1:59:12.461 --> 1:59:15.089
either get a safety razor
or grow a beard.

1:59:23.505 --> 1:59:25.439
[ Knocking ]

1:59:28.110 --> 1:59:31.273
- Is Mr. Greenleaf here ?
- Mr. Ripley ?

1:59:31.346 --> 1:59:34.042
- Yes.
- I'm Alvin MacCarron.

1:59:36.718 --> 1:59:39.414
[ Marge ] I don't know,
I don't know. I just know it.

1:59:39.488 --> 1:59:42.423
[ Mr. Greenleaf ] Marge, there's female
intuition and then there are facts.

1:59:44.993 --> 1:59:46.927
- Tom.
- Sir.

1:59:46.995 --> 1:59:49.725
Marge, you should have waited.
I didn't--

1:59:49.798 --> 1:59:52.460
Didn't Peter say I'd
come by and pick you up ?

1:59:53.602 --> 1:59:56.196
Marge has been telling us
about the rings.

1:59:56.271 --> 1:59:58.762
Yes, I feel ridiculous
I didn't mention them yesterday.

1:59:58.840 --> 2:00:01.274
I clean forgot.
Ridiculous.

2:00:03.845 --> 2:00:08.145
Perhaps you didn't mention them because
there's only one conclusion to be drawn.

2:00:10.218 --> 2:00:13.483
I'm going to take Marge for a walk.
Tom, Mr. MacCarron needs to talk to you.

2:00:13.555 --> 2:00:15.785
There's no need. We could go
to the bar. There's no need.

2:00:15.857 --> 2:00:18.052
No, no.

2:00:18.126 --> 2:00:20.390
I think you should
stay here.

2:00:22.898 --> 2:00:26.061
[ Door Opening, Closing ]

2:00:42.250 --> 2:00:44.741
I could probably
see my room from here.

2:00:44.820 --> 2:00:46.754
I can see my house.

2:00:48.757 --> 2:00:52.887
When you see where you live from a
distance, it's like a dream, isn't it ?

2:00:52.961 --> 2:00:55.225
I don't care for B.S.

2:00:55.297 --> 2:00:57.925
I don't care to hear it.
I don't care to speak it.

2:01:00.168 --> 2:01:02.432
- Okay.
- Did you know that at Princeton...

2:01:02.504 --> 2:01:04.836
Dickie Greenleaf
half-killed a boy ?

2:01:05.907 --> 2:01:07.932
At a party over some girl.

2:01:08.010 --> 2:01:11.878
Kicked the kid several times
in the head, put him in the hospital.

2:01:11.947 --> 2:01:15.781
Boy had a wire fixed in his jaw,
lost some hearing.

2:01:15.851 --> 2:01:19.150
Why do you think Dickie's father
sent him to Europe in the first place ?

2:01:21.857 --> 2:01:26.055
The Rome police didn't think
to ask Mr. Greenleaf.

2:01:26.128 --> 2:01:29.120
Nor did they think to check
on whether a Thomas Ripley...

2:01:29.197 --> 2:01:32.360
had ever been a student
at Princeton University.

2:01:32.434 --> 2:01:37.064
Oh, I turned up
a Tom Ripley...

2:01:37.139 --> 2:01:41.235
who had been a piano tuner
in the music department.

2:01:42.310 --> 2:01:44.403
You see, in America,

2:01:44.479 --> 2:01:49.007
we are taught to check a fact
before it becomes a fact.

2:01:49.084 --> 2:01:51.484
We're taught to nose around.

2:01:51.553 --> 2:01:54.420
When a girl drowns herself,

2:01:54.489 --> 2:01:56.889
find out if
that girl is pregnant.

2:01:56.958 --> 2:01:59.893
Find out if Dickie
had an embarrassment there.

2:02:01.296 --> 2:02:04.663
Mr. Greenleaf appreciates your loyalty.
He really does.

2:02:04.733 --> 2:02:07.793
Marge--
She has a hundred theories.

2:02:07.869 --> 2:02:10.804
There are a few things
that she doesn't know.

2:02:10.872 --> 2:02:12.863
We hope she never knows.

2:02:12.941 --> 2:02:15.171
I hope she never knows.

2:02:15.243 --> 2:02:17.734
Three different people...

2:02:17.813 --> 2:02:21.374
saw Dickie
get into Freddie's car.

2:02:21.450 --> 2:02:24.749
One man,
who will not testify...

2:02:24.820 --> 2:02:27.755
because he was jumping somebody
else's wife at the time,

2:02:27.823 --> 2:02:31.816
saw Dickie removing license plates
from a red sports car.

2:02:31.893 --> 2:02:35.886
The police know about this man because
he happens to be a policeman.

2:02:37.933 --> 2:02:41.391
I found these in the basement
of Dickie's apartment.

2:02:41.470 --> 2:02:43.563
They belong to Freddie's car.

2:02:43.638 --> 2:02:47.938
Mr. Greenleaf has asked me...

2:02:48.009 --> 2:02:50.910
to lose these in the canal
this evening.

2:02:53.381 --> 2:02:56.009
[ Bell Tolling ]

2:02:56.084 --> 2:02:58.951
Mr. Greenleaf feels that
there was a silent promise...

2:02:59.020 --> 2:03:02.183
in Dickie's letter to you
which he intends to honor.

2:03:02.257 --> 2:03:04.817
He also intends to transfer
a good portion...

2:03:04.893 --> 2:03:09.626
of Dickie's income from his trust
into your name.

2:03:09.698 --> 2:03:11.791
He does not intend...

2:03:11.867 --> 2:03:15.325
to give the Italians any
information about Dickie's past.

2:03:17.272 --> 2:03:21.106
He's rather hoping that...
you will feel the same.

2:03:39.127 --> 2:03:41.061
- Thank you so much, Tom.
- Sir.

2:03:41.129 --> 2:03:43.063
Good-bye.

2:03:47.702 --> 2:03:52.002
Marge, I feel I never should have said
those things to you the other evening.

2:03:52.073 --> 2:03:56.100
I was pretty flustered,
and the rings-- And you looked so--

2:03:56.178 --> 2:03:58.442
I don't know.

2:03:58.513 --> 2:04:02.574
But I hope that note goes
in your purse to New York...

2:04:02.651 --> 2:04:05.119
for a rainy day.

2:04:06.688 --> 2:04:10.385
- What are you gonna do now, Tom ?
- I don't know.

2:04:10.458 --> 2:04:12.585
Peter has a concert in Athens
next month,

2:04:12.661 --> 2:04:15.255
so he asked me to come along
and help out.

2:04:17.832 --> 2:04:19.766
He says good-bye.

2:04:19.834 --> 2:04:21.802
By the way, he was
in rehearsal so he couldn't--

2:04:21.870 --> 2:04:26.068
Why do I think there's
never been a Ripley rainy day ?

2:04:26.141 --> 2:04:28.735
What ?

2:04:28.810 --> 2:04:32.541
I know it was you.
I know it was you.

2:04:32.614 --> 2:04:35.447
I know it was you !
I know it was you !

2:04:35.517 --> 2:04:39.180
- Marge, Marge. Please !
- I know you killed Dickie !

2:04:39.254 --> 2:04:41.188
- Marge !
- I know ! No !

2:04:41.256 --> 2:04:44.748
[ Sobbing ]
I know it was you !

2:04:44.826 --> 2:04:46.851
Marge.
Marge, please.

2:04:46.928 --> 2:04:49.590
It's not Tom.
Really.

2:04:58.173 --> 2:05:01.438
[ Tom And Peter ]
#We are called gondoleri #

2:05:01.509 --> 2:05:05.468
# But that's a vagary
It's quite honorary #

2:05:05.680 --> 2:05:10.999
# The trade that we ply ##

2:05:11.133 --> 2:05:13.863
Ask me what I want to change
about this moment.

2:05:13.936 --> 2:05:16.404
I don't know. What do you want
to change about this moment ?

2:05:16.472 --> 2:05:18.167
Nothing.

2:05:21.844 --> 2:05:24.642
[ Peter ]
I'm freezing. Coming down ?

2:05:24.713 --> 2:05:27.546
Later. I want
to catch the sunset.

2:05:27.616 --> 2:05:31.882
- You're mad. [ Chuckling ]
- I am.

2:05:41.797 --> 2:05:43.731
[ Meredith ]
Dickie ?

2:05:46.935 --> 2:05:48.869
Dickie ?

2:05:52.274 --> 2:05:54.208
Dickie!

2:06:01.183 --> 2:06:04.084
[ Italian ]

2:06:05.287 --> 2:06:07.221
Oh, my God.

2:06:09.191 --> 2:06:11.125
Hello, Meredith.

2:06:14.263 --> 2:06:16.595
I was looking at you.

2:06:16.665 --> 2:06:20.101
Your clothes.
I wouldn't have known you.

2:06:20.169 --> 2:06:22.933
Well, you spotted me,
so you get the reward.

2:06:24.606 --> 2:06:27.268
- What ?
-Just kidding.

2:06:27.342 --> 2:06:31.301
- Are you alone ?
- Oh.

2:06:31.380 --> 2:06:34.406
Hardly.
Couldn't be less alone.

2:06:34.483 --> 2:06:37.145
- Aunt Joan.
- And " co."

2:06:40.289 --> 2:06:42.257
A lot of " co."

2:06:43.392 --> 2:06:46.520
Oh, God.

2:06:46.595 --> 2:06:49.689
You know, seeing you again, l--

2:06:51.767 --> 2:06:55.032
I've thought about you...

2:06:55.103 --> 2:06:57.037
so much.

2:06:57.105 --> 2:06:59.039
And I've thought about you.

2:07:01.109 --> 2:07:04.545
Yeah, well, when I've thought about you,
I was mostly hating you.

2:07:11.153 --> 2:07:13.121
Where have you been hiding ?

2:07:13.188 --> 2:07:16.715
I haven't been hiding.

2:07:16.792 --> 2:07:19.124
I've been in police custody.

2:07:20.462 --> 2:07:23.397
They've been trying to
flush out Freddie's killer.

2:07:23.465 --> 2:07:26.662
- You're kidding.
- They're giving me this vacation,

2:07:26.735 --> 2:07:29.033
which is why
the getup.

2:07:29.104 --> 2:07:31.265
Which is why
you haven't heard from me.

2:07:31.340 --> 2:07:33.638
You know, the whole world
thinks you killed Freddie.

2:07:33.709 --> 2:07:36.803
- Oh ! It's terrible.
- I know.

2:07:36.879 --> 2:07:39.575
Listen, I can't
talk now. Um, later ?

